line 112=>at the hobbit without saying anything, till Bilbo got quite uncomfortable and even 
line 113=>a little cross. 
line 114=>"Good  morning!"  he  said  at  last.  "We  don't  want  any  adventures  here,  thank 
line 115=>you! You might try over The Hill or across The Water." By this he meant that the 
line 116=>conversation was at an end. 
line 117=>"What a lot of things you do use Good morning for!" said Gandalf. "Now you 
line 118=>mean that you want to get rid of me, and that it won't be good till I move off." 
line 119=>"Not  at  all,  not  at  all,  my  dear  sir!  Let  me  see,  I  don't  think  I  know  your 
