line 184=>time.  But  it  was  not  Gandalf.  Instead  there  was  a  very  old-looking  dwarf  on  the 
line 185=>step with a white beard and a scarlet hood; and he too hopped inside as soon as the 
line 186=>door was open, just as if he had been invited. 
line 187=>"I  see  they  have  begun  to  arrive  already,"  he  said  when  he  caught  sight  of 
line 188=>Dwalin's  green  hood  hanging  up.  He  hung  his  red  one  next  to  it,  and  "Balin  at 
line 189=>your service!" he said with his hand on his breast. 
line 190=>"Thank  you!"  said  Bilbo with  a  gasp.  It was  not  the  correct  thing  to  say,  but 
