line 192=>to know  them before  they arrived, and he preferred  to ask  them himself. He had a 
line 193=>horrible  thought  that  the  cakes might  run  short,  and  then  he-as  the host: he knew 
line 194=>his duty and stuck to it however painful-he might have to go without. 
line 195=>"Come  along  in,  and  have  some  tea!"  he  managed  to  say  after  taking  a  deep 
line 196=>breath. 
line 197=>
line 198=>####-"A  little  beer  would  suit  me  better,  if  it  is  all  the  same  to  you, my  good  sir," 
line 199=>said  Balin  with  the  white  beard.  "But  I  don't  mind  some  cake-seed-cake,  if  you 
line 200=>have any." 
line 201=>"Lots!"  Bilbo  found  himself  answering,  to  his  own  surprise;  and  he  found 
line 202=>himself  scuttling  off,  too,  to  the  cellar  to  fill  a  pint  beer-mug, and to the pantry to 
line 203=>fetch  two  beautiful  round  seed-cakes  which  he  had  baked  that  afternoon  for  his 
line 204=>after-supper morsel. 
line 205=>When he got back Balin and Dwalin were  talking at  the  table  like old  friends 
