line 213=>"What can I do for you, my dwarves?" he said. "Kili at your service!" said the 
line 214=>one.  "And  Fili!"  added  the  other;  and  they  both  swept  off  their  blue  hoods  and 
line 215=>bowed. 
line 216=>"At  yours  and  your  family's!"  replied  Bilbo,  remembering  his  manners  this 
line 217=>time. 
line 218=>"Dwalin and Balin here already, I see," said Kili. "Let us join the throng!" 
line 219=>"Throng!" thought Mr. Baggins. "I don't like the sound of that. I really must sit 
line 220=>down for a minute and collect my wits, and have a drink." He had only just had a 
line 221=>sip-in  the  corner,  while  the  four  dwarves  sat  around  the  table,  and  talked  about 
