line 259=>For  one  thing  Bombur  was  immensely  fat  and  heavy.  Thorin  indeed  was  very 
line 260=>haughty,  and  said  nothing  about  service;  but  poor Mr. Baggins  said  he was  sorry 
line 261=>so  many  times,  that  at  last  he  grunted  "pray  don't  mention  it,"  and  stopped 
line 262=>frowning. 
line 263=>"Now we  are  all here!"  said Gandalf,  looking  at  the  row of  thirteen hoods-the 
line 264=>best  detachable  party  hoods-and his own hat hanging on  the pegs. "Quite a merry 
line 265=>gathering! 
line 266=>I hope there is something left for the late-comers to eat and drink! What's that? 
line 267=>Tea! No thank you! A little red wine, I think, for me." "And for me," said Thorin. 
