line 275=>"Seems  to  know  as  much  about  the  inside  of  my  larders  as  I  do  myself!" 
line 276=>thought Mr. Baggins, who was  feeling  positively  flummoxed,  and was  beginning 
line 277=>to wonder whether  a most wretched  adventure  had  not  come  right  into his house. 
