line 926=>really  first-class  and  legendary  burglar would  at  this  point  have  picked  the  trolls' 
line 927=>pockets-it  is  nearly  always  worthwhile  if  you  can  manage  it-,  pinched  the  very 
line 928=>mutton off the spite, purloined the beer, and walked off without their noticing him. 
line 929=>Others more practical but with less professional pride would perhaps have stuck a 
line 930=>dagger  into  each  of  them  before  they observed  it. Then  the night could have been 
line 931=>spent cheerily.  
line 932=>Bilbo knew  it. He had  read of a good many  things he had never seen or done. 
line 933=>He  was  very  much  alarmed,  as  well  as  disgusted;  he  wished  himself  a  hundred 
