line 1515=>off  to  sleep  one  by  one.  And  that  was  the  last  time  that  they  used  the  ponies, 
line 1516=>packages, baggages, tools and paraphernalia that they had brought with them. 
line 1517=>It  turned  out  a  good  thing  that  night  that  they  had  brought  little  Bilbo  with 
line 1518=>them, after all. For somehow, he could not go  to sleep for a  long while; and when 
line 1519=>he did sleep, he had very nasty dreams. He dreamed that a crack in the wall at the 
line 1520=>back  of  the  cave  got  bigger  and  bigger,  and  opened wider  and wider,  and  he was 
line 1521=>
