line 1523=>dreamed  that  the floor of  the cave was giving way, and he was slipping-beginning 
line 1524=>to fall down, down, goodness knows where to. 
line 1525=>At  that he woke up with a horrible start, and found  that part of his dream was 
line 1526=>true. A crack had opened at the back of the cave, and was already a wide passage. 
line 1527=>He  was  just  in  time  to  see  the  last  of  the  ponies'  tails  disappearing  into  it.  Of 
line 1528=>course  he  gave  a  very  loud  yell,  as  loud  a  yell  as  a  hobbit  can  give,  which  is 
line 1529=>surprising for their size. 
line 1530=>Out  jumped  the  goblins,  big  goblins,  great  ugly-looking  goblins,  lots  of 
