line 1631=>"We were on a journey to visit our relatives, our nephews and nieces, and first, 
line 1632=>second, and third cousins, and the other descendants of our grandfathers, who live 
line 1633=>on  the  East  side  of  these  truly  hospitable  mountains,"  said  Thorin,  not  quite 
line 1634=>knowing  what  to  say  all  at  once  in  a  moment,  when  obviously  the  exact  truth 
line 1635=>would not do at all. 
line 1636=>"He is a liar, O truly tremendous one!" said one of the drivers. "Several of our 
line 1637=>people  were  struck  by  lightning  in  the  cave,  when  we  invited  these  creatures  to 
line 1638=>come  below;  and  they  are  as  dead  as  stones. Also  he  has  not  explained  this!" He 
line 1639=>
line 1640=>####-held out the sword which Thorin had worn, the sword which came from the Trolls' 
line 1641=>lair.  
line 1642=>The Great Goblin gave a truly awful howl of rage when he looked at it, and all 
line 1643=>his soldiers gnashed their teeth, clashed their shields, and stamped. They knew the 
line 1644=>sword at once.  It had killed hundreds of goblins  in  its  time, when  the  fair elves of 
line 1645=>Gondolin hunted them in the hills or did battle before their walls. They had called 
line 1646=>it Orcrist, Goblin-cleaver, but the goblins called it simply Biter. They hated it and 
line 1647=>hated worse any one that carried it. 
line 1648=>"Murderers'  and  elf-friends!"  the  Great  Goblin  shouted.  "Slash  them!  Beat 
line 1649=>them! Bite  them! Gnash  them! Take  them  away  to  dark  holes  full  of  snakes,  and 
line 1650=>never  let  them  see  the  light  again!" He was  in  such  a  rage  that he  jumped off his 
line 1651=>seat and himself rushed at Thorin with his mouth open. 
line 1652=>Just  at  that  moment  all  the  lights  in  the  cavern  went  out,  and  the  great  fire 
line 1653=>went  off  poof!  into  a  tower  of  blue  glowing  smoke,  right  up  to  the  roof,  that 
