line 1692=>fourteen!  Well,  well!  it  might  be  worse,  and  then  again  it  might  be  a  good  deal 
line 1693=>better. No ponies, and no food, and no knowing quite where we are, and hordes of 
line 1694=>angry goblins just behind! On we go!" 
line 1695=>On  they  went.  Gandalf  was  quite  right:  they  began  to  hear  goblin  noises  and 
line 1696=>horrible cries far behind in the passages they had come through. That sent them on 
line 1697=>faster  than  ever,  and  as  poor Bilbo  could  not  possibly  go  half  as  fast-for dwarves 
line 1698=>can roll along at a tremendous pace, I can tell you, when they have to-they took it 
line 1699=>in turn to carry him on their backs. 
line 1700=>Still  goblins  go  faster  than  dwarves,  and  these  goblins  knew  the  way  better 
line 1701=>(they had made the paths themselves), and were madly angry; so that do what they 
line 1702=>could  the  dwarves  heard  the  cries  and  howls  getting  closer  and  closer.  Soon  they 
