line 1704=>just  round  the  last  corner.  The  blink  of  red  torches  could  be  seen  behind  them  in 
line 1705=>the tunnel they were following; and they were getting deadly tired. 
line 1706=>"Why,  O  why  did  I  ever  leave  my  hobbit-hole!"  said  poor  Mr.  Baggins 
line 1707=>bumping up and down on Bombur's back. 
line 1708=>"Why, O why did I ever bring a wretched little hobbit on a treasure hunt!" said 
line 1709=>poor Bombur, who was fat, and staggered along with the sweat dripping down his 
