line 2067=>"Both  wrong,"  cried  Bilbo  very much  relieved;  and  he  jumped  at  once  to  his 
line 2068=>feet,  put  his  back  to  the  nearest  wall,  and  held  out  his  little  sword.  He  knew,  of 
line 2069=>course,  that  the  riddle-game  was  sacred  and  of  immense  antiquity,  and  even 
line 2070=>wicked creatures were afraid  to cheat when  they played at  it. But he  felt he could 
line 2071=>not trust this slimy thing to keep any promise at a pinch. Any excuse would do for 
line 2072=>him to slide out of it. And after all that last question had not been a genuine riddle 
line 2073=>according to the ancient laws. 
line 2074=>But at any  rate Gollum did not at once attack him. He could  see  the  sword  in 
line 2075=>Bilbo's  hand.  He  sat  still,  shivering  and  whispering.  At  last  Bilbo  could  wait  no 
