line 2295=>They saw him sooner than he saw them. Yes, they saw him. Whether it was .an 
line 2296=>accident,  or  a  last  trick  of  the  ring  before  it  took  a  new master,  it was  not  on  his 
line 2297=>finger. With yells of delight the goblins rushed upon him. 
line 2298=>A  pang  of  fear  and  loss,  like  an  echo  of  Gollum's  misery,  smote  Bilbo,  and 
line 2299=>forgetting even  to draw his sword he struck his hands  into his pockets. And- there 
line 2300=>was  the  ring  still,  in  his  left  pocket,  and  it  slipped  on  his  finger.  The  goblins 
line 2301=>stopped  short.  They  could  not  see  a  sign  of  him.  He  had  vanished.  They  yelled 
line 2302=>twice as loud as before, but not so delightedly.  
line 2303=>"Where is it?" they cried. 
line 2304=>"Go back up the passage!" some shouted. 
line 2305=>"This way!" some yelled. "That way!" others yelled. 
line 2306=>"Look out for the door," bellowed the captain. 
line 2307=>Whistles  blew,  armour  clashed,  swords  rattled,  goblins  cursed  and  swore  and 
