line 2448=>The wizard, to tell the truth, never minded explaining his cleverness more than 
line 2449=>once, so now he had told Bilbo that both he and Elrond had been well aware of the 
line 2450=>presence of evil goblins  in  that part of  the mountains. But  their main gate used  to 
line 2451=>come out on a different pass, one more easy to travel by, so that they often caught 
line 2452=>people  benighted  near  their  gates. Evidently  people  had  given  up  going  that way, 
line 2453=>and  the  goblins  must  have  opened  their  new  entrance  at  the  top  of  the  pass  the 
line 2454=>dwarves had taken, quite recently, because it had been found quite safe up to now.  
line 2455=>
