line 2481=>footsteps  for  hours  and  hours  after  we  have  passed. We  must  be  miles  on  before 
line 2482=>dusk. There will be a bit of moon,  if  it keeps fine, and  that  is  lucky. Not  that  they 
line 2483=>mind the moon much, but it will give us a little light to steer by." 
line 2484=>"O yes!" he said  in answer  to more questions from  the hobbit. "You  lose  track 
line 2485=>of  time  inside  goblin-tunnels.  Today's  Thursday,  and  it  was  Monday  night  or 
line 2486=>Tuesday morning that we were captured. We have gone miles and miles, and come 
