line 2498=>nicely to let you have your pony back and your luggage." 
line 2499=>"No thank you!" said Bilbo. 
line 2500=>"Very well  then, we must  just  tighten our belts  and  trudge on  - or  we shall be 
line 2501=>made into supper, and that will be much worse than having none ourselves." 
line 2502=>As  they went  on  Bilbo  looked  from  side  to  side  for  something  to  eat;  but  the 
line 2503=>blackberries were  still  only  in  flower,  and  of  course  there were  no  nuts,  nor  even 
line 2504=>hawthorn-berries. He nibbled a bit of sorrel, and he drank from a small mountain-
line 2505=>stream that crossed the path, and he ate three wild strawberries that he found on its 
line 2506=>bank, but it was not much good. 
line 2507=>They  still  went  on  and  on.  The  rough  path  disappeared.  The  bushes,  and  the 
line 2508=>long  grasses,  between  the  boulders,  the  patches  of  rabbit-cropped  turf,  the  thyme 
line 2509=>and  the  sage  and  the  marjoram,  and  the  yellow  rockroses  all  vanished,  and  they 
line 2510=>found themselves at the top of a wide steep slope of fallen stones, the remains of a 
line 2511=>landslide.  When  they  began  to  go  down  this,  rubbish  and  small  pebbles  rolled 
line 2512=>away  from  their  feet;  soon  larger  bits  of  split  stone  went  clattering  down  and 
line 2513=>started  other  pieces  below  them  slithering  and  rolling;  then  lumps  of  rocks  were 
line 2514=>disturbed and bounded off, crashing down with a dust and a noise. Before long the 
line 2515=>whole  slope  above  them  and  below  them  seemed  on  the  move,  and  they  were 
line 2516=>sliding  away,  huddled  all  together,  in  a  fearful  confusion  of  slipping,  rattling, 
line 2517=>cracking slabs and stones. 
line 2518=>It  was  the  trees  at  the  bottom  that  saved  them.  They  slid  into  the  edge  of  a 
line 2519=>climbing  wood  of  pines  that  here  stood  right  up  the  mountain  slope  from  the 
line 2520=>deeper  darker  forests  of  the  valleys  below.  Some  caught  hold  of  the  trunks  and 
line 2521=>swung  themselves  into  lower  branches,  some  (like  the  little  hobbit)  got  behind  a 
line 2522=>tree to shelter from the onslaught of the rocks. Soon the danger was over, the slide 
line 2523=>had  stopped,  and  the  last  faint  crashes  could  be  heard  as  the  largest  of  the 
line 2524=>disturbed  stones  went  bounding  and  spinning  among  the  bracken  and  the  pine-
line 2525=>roots far below.  
line 2526=>"Well!  that  has  got  us  on  a  bit,"  said  Gandalf;  "and  even  goblins  tracking  us 
line 2527=>will have a job to come down here quietly." 
line 2528=>
line 2529=>####-"I  daresay,"  grumbled Bombur;  "but  they won't  find  it  difficult  to  send  stones 
