line 3031=>Inside  on  the  southward  side  of  the  great  hedge were  rows  and  rows  of  hives 
line 3032=>with  bell-shaped  tops made of  straw. The noise of  the giant bees  flying  to and  fro 
line 3033=>and crawling in and out filled all the air.  
line 3034=>The  wizard  and  the  hobbit  pushed  open  the  heavy  creaking  gate  and  went 
