line 3426=>all  the  advice  I  can  give  you.  Beyond  the  edge  of  the  forest  I  cannot  help  you 
line 3427=>much;  you must  depend  on  your  luck  and  your  courage  and  the  food  I  send with 
line 3428=>you. At the gate of the forest I must ask you to send back my horse and my ponies. 
line 3429=>But I wish you all speed, and my house is open to you, if ever you come back this 
line 3430=>way again." 
line 3431=>They  thanked  him,  of  course,  with  many  bows  and  sweepings  of  their  hoods 
