line 3820=>expect  they were a kind of  'purple emperor,' a butterfly  that  loves  the  tops of oak-
line 3821=>woods,  but  these  were  not  purple  at  all,  they  were  a  dark  dark  velvety  black 
line 3822=>without any markings to be seen. 
line 3823=>He  looked  at  the  'black  emperors'  for  a  long  time,  and  enjoyed  the  feel  of  the 
line 3824=>breeze in his hair and on his face; but at length the cries of the dwarves, who were 
line 3825=>now  simply  stamping  with  impatience  down  below,  reminded  him  of  his  real 
