line 3874=>Bombur  kept  on wailing  that  his  legs would  not  carry  him  and  that  he wanted  to 
line 3875=>lie down and sleep. 
line 3876=>"No you don't!" they said. "Let your legs take their share, we have carried you 
line 3877=>far enough." 
line 3878=>All  the same he suddenly refused  to go a step further and flung himself on  the 
line 3879=>ground.  "Go  on,  if  you  must,"  he  said.  "I'm  just  going  to  lie  here  and  sleep  and 
line 3880=>dream of food, if I can't get it any other way. I hope I never wake up again." 
line 3881=>At that very moment Balin, who was a little way ahead, called out: "What was 
line 3882=>that? I thought I saw a twinkle of light in the forest." 
line 3883=>They  all  looked,  and  a  longish  way  off,  it  seemed,  they  saw  a  red  twinkle  in 
line 3884=>the dark; then another and another sprang out beside it. Even Bombur got up, and 
line 3885=>they hurried along then, not caring if it was trolls or goblins. The light was in front 
line 3886=>of them and to the left of the path, and when at last they had drawn level with it, it 
line 3887=>seemed  plain  that  torches  and  fires were  burning  under  the  trees, but a good way 
line 3888=>off their track. 
line 3889=>
line 3890=>####-"It  looks  as  if  my  dreams  were  coming  true,"  gasped  Bombur  puffing  up 
line 3891=>behind. He wanted to rush straight off into the wood after the lights. But the others 
line 3892=>remembered  only  too  well  the  warnings  of  the  wizard  and  of  Beorn.  "A  feast 
line 3893=>would be no good, if we never got back alive from it," said Thorin. 
line 3894=>"But  without  a  feast  we  shan't  remain  alive  much  longer  anyway,"  said 
