line 3896=>forwards for a long while, until they agreed at length to send out a couple of spies, 
line 3897=>to  creep  near  the  lights  and  find  out  more  about  them.  But  then  they  could  not 
line 3898=>agree  on  who  was  to  be  sent:  no  one  seemed  anxious  to  run  the  chance  of  being 
line 3899=>lost  and  never  finding  his  friends  again.  In  the  end,  in  spite  of  warnings,  hunger 
line 3900=>decided  them,  because  Bombur  kept  on  describing  all  the  good  things  that  were 
