line 3968=>collars and their belts; and their faces and their songs were filled with mirth. Loud 
line 3969=>and clear and fair were those songs, and out stepped Thorin into their midst. 
line 3970=>Dead  silence  fell  in  the middle of  a word. Out went  all  light. The  fires  leaped 
line 3971=>up  in  black  smokes.  Ashes  and  cinders  were  in  the  eyes  of  the  dwarves,  and  the 
line 3972=>wood  was  filled  again  with  their  clamour  and  their  cries.  Bilbo  found  himself 
