line 3988=>hand,  and when  he  tried  to move  he  found  that  his  legs were  already wrapped  in 
line 3989=>the same stuff, so that when he got up he fell over.  
line 3990=>Then  the great  spider, who had been busy  tying him up while he dozed, came 
line 3991=>from  behind  him  and  came  at  him.  He  could  only  see  the  things's  eyes,  but  he 
line 3992=>could  feel  its  hairy  legs  as  it  struggled  to wind  its  abominable  threads  round  and 
line 3993=>round him. It was lucky that he had come to his senses in time. Soon he would not 
