line 4606=>brings  deep  and  pleasant  dreams.  There  would  be  a  different  expression  on  the 
line 4607=>face of  the  chief guard next day,  even  though Bilbo, before  they went on,  stole  in 
line 4608=>and kindheartedly put the keys back on his belt. 
line 4609=>"That  will  save  him  some  of  the  trouble  he  is  in  for,"  said  Mr.  Baggins  to 
line 4610=>himself.  "He wasn't  a  bad  fellow,  and  quite  decent  to  the  prisoners.  It will  puzzle 
line 4611=>them all too. They will think we had a very strong magic to pass through all those 
line 4612=>locked doors and disappear. Disappear! We have got to get busy very quick, if that 
line 4613=>is to happen!" 
line 4614=> 
line 4615=>Balin was  told  off  to watch  the  guard  and  the  butler  and  give warning  if  they 
