line 4640=>as  they  could.  "Where's  old  Galion,  the  butler?"  said  one.  "I  haven't  seen  him  at 
line 4641=>the tables tonight. He ought to be here now to show us what is to be done." 
line 4642=>"I shall be angry  if  the old slowcoach  is  late," said another. "I have no wish  to 
line 4643=>waste time down here while the song is up!" 
line 4644=>"Ha, ha!" came a cry. "Here's  the old villain with his head on a jug! He's been 
line 4645=>having a little feast all to himself and his friend the captain." 
line 4646=>"Shake him! Wake him!" shouted the others impatiently. Gallon was not at all 
