line 5407=>but  calculating  folk with  a great  idea of  the value of money;  some  are  tricky  and 
line 5408=>
line 5409=>####-treacherous  and  pretty  bad  lots;  some  are  not,  but  are  decent  enough  people  like 
line 5410=>Thorin and Company, if you don't expect too much. 
line 5411=> 
line 5412=>The  stars  were  coming  out  behind  him  in  a  pale  sky  barred  with  black  when 
line 5413=>the hobbit crept through the enchanted door and stole into the Mountain. It was far 
line 5414=>easier going  than he  expected. This was no goblin  entrance, or  rough wood-elves' 
line 5415=>cave.  It  was  a  passage  made  by  dwarves,  at  the  height  of  their  wealth  and  skill: 
line 5416=>straight  as  a  ruler,  smooth-floored  and  smooth-sided,  going  with  a  gentle  never-
line 5417=>varying slope direct-to some distant end in the blackness below.  
line 5418=>After a while Balin bade Bilbo "Good  luck!" and  stopped where he could still 
line 5419=>see the faint outline of the door, and by a trick of, the echoes of the tunnel hear the 
line 5420=>rustle  of  the whispering  voices  of  the  others  just  outside. Then  the  hobbit  slipped 
