line 5426=>in its sheath, tightened his belt, and went on. 
line 5427=> 
line 5428=>"Now  you  are  in  for  it  at  last, Bilbo Baggins,"  he  said  to  himself.  "You went 
line 5429=>and put your foot right in it that night of the party, and now you have got to pull it 
line 5430=>out and pay for it! Dear me, what a fool I was and am!" said the least Tookish part 
line 5431=>of  him.  "I  have  absolutely  no  use  for  dragon-guarded treasures, and the whole lot 
line 5432=>could  stay  here  for  ever,  if  only  I  could wake up and  find  this beastly  tunnel was 
line 5433=>my own front-hall at home!" 
line 5434=>He did not wake up of course, but went still on and on, till all sign of the door 
