line 5969=>above him and far off in the gloom. But certainly it was not a spark of dragon-fire, 
line 5970=>though the wormstench was heavy in the place, and the taste of vapour was on his 
line 5971=>tongue. 
line 5972=>At length Mr. Baggins could bear it no longer. "Come found you, Smaug, you 
line 5973=>worm!"  he  squeaked  aloud.  "Stop  playing  hide-and-seek!  Give  me  a  light,  and 
line 5974=>then eat me if you can catch me!" 
line 5975=>Faint echoes ran round the unseen hall, but there was no answer. Bilbo got up, 
line 5976=>and found that he did not know in what direction to turn. 
line 5977=>"Now  I  wonder  what  on  earth  Smaug  is  playing  at,"  he  said.  "He  is  not  at 
