line 6551=>way,  and  carrion birds  are with  them hoping  for battle  and  slaughter. By  the  lake 
line 6552=>men murmur  that  their sorrows are due  to  the dwarves; for  they are homeless and 
line 6553=>
line 6554=>####-many  have  died,  and  Smaug  has  destroyed  their  town.  They  too  think  to  find 
line 6555=>amends from your treasure, whether you are alive or dead. 
line 6556=>"Your  own wisdom must  decide  your  course,  but  thirteen  is  small  remnant  of 
line 6557=>the great folk of Durin that once dwelt here, and now are scattered far. If you will 
