line 6851=>partly wrapped in an old blanket, was something new to them. 
line 6852=>"Really you know," Bilbo was  saying  in his best business manner,  "things  are 
line 6853=>impossible. Personally I am tired of the whole affair. I wish I was back in the West 
line 6854=>in  my  own  home,  where  folk  are  more  reasonable.  But  I  have  an  interest  in  this 
line 6855=>matter-one  fourteenth share,  to be precise, according  to a  letter, which  fortunately 
line 6856=>I believe I have kept." He drew from a pocket in his old jacket (which he still wore 
line 6857=>over his mail), crumpled and much folded, Thorin's letter that had been put under 
