line 6898=>like to me. I hope you will find it useful." 
line 6899=>The Elvenking looked at Bilbo with a new wonder.  
line 6900=>"Bilbo  Baggins!"  he  said.  "You  are  more  worthy  to  wear  the  armour  of  elf-
line 6901=>princes  than  many  that  have  looked  more  comely  in  it.  But  I  wonder  if  Thorin 
line 6902=>Oakenshield will see it so. I have more knowledge of dwarves  in general than you 
line 6903=>have perhaps. I advise you to remain with us, and here you shall be honoured and 
line 6904=>thrice welcome." 
line 6905=>"Thank you very much I am sure," said Bilbo with a bow. "But I don't think I 
line 6906=>ought to leave my friends like this, after all we have gone through together. And I 
line 6907=>promised  to  wake  old  Bombur  at  midnight,  too!  Really  I  must  be  going,  and 
line 6908=>quickly." 
line 6909=>Nothing  they  could  say  would  stop  him;  so  an  escort  was  provided  for  him, 
line 6910=>and  as  he  went  both  the  king  and  Bard  saluted  him  with  honour.  As  they  passed 
line 6911=>
