line 6913=>where he was sitting and came towards them. 
line 6914=>"Well  done!  Mr.  Baggins!"  he  said,  clapping  Bilbo  on  the  back.  "There  is 
line 6915=>always more about you than anyone expects!" It was Gandalf. 
line 6916=>For the first time for many a day Bilbo was really delighted. But there was no 
line 6917=>time for all the questions that he immediately wished to ask. 
line 6918=>"All  in  good  time!"  said  Gandalf.  "Things  are  drawing  towards  the  end  now, 
line 6919=>unless  I  am  mistaken.  There  is  an  unpleasant  time  just  in  front  of  you;  but  keep 
line 6920=>your heart up! You may  come  through  all  right. There  is news brewing  that  even 
line 6921=>the ravens have not heard. Good night!" 
line 6922=>Puzzled  but  cheered.  Bilbo  hurried  on.  He  was  guided  to  a  safe  ford  and  set 
line 6923=>across  dry,  and  then  he  said  farewell  to  the  elves  and  climbed  carefully  back 
line 6924=>towards the Gate. Great weariness began to come over him; but it was well before 
line 6925=>midnight when he  clambered up  the  rope  again  â€“  it was  still where he had  left  it. 
line 6926=>He untied  it and hid  it, and  then he sat down on the wall and wondered anxiously 
line 6927=>what would happen next. 
line 6928=>At  midnight  he  woke  up  Bombur;  and  then  in  turn  rolled  himself  up  in  his 
line 6929=>corner,  without  listening  to  old  dwarfs  thanks  (which  he  felt  he  had  hardly 
line 6930=>earned).  He  was  soon  fast  asleep  forgetting  all  his  worries  till  the  morning.  As 
line 6931=>matter of fact he was dreaming of eggs and bacon. 
