line 6983=>to say, you descendant of rats?" 
line 6984=>"Dear  me!  Dear  me!"  said  Bilbo.  "I  am  sure  this  is  all  very  uncomfortable. 
line 6985=>You may remember saying that I might choose my own fourteenth share? Perhaps 
line 6986=>I took it too literally â€“1 have been told that dwarves are sometimes politer in word 
line 6987=>than  in  deed.  The  time  was,  all  the  same,  when  you  seemed  to  think  that  I  had 
line 6988=>been of some service. Descendant of rats, indeed! Is this ail the service of you and 
line 6989=>your family that I was promised. Thorin? Take it that I have disposed of my share 
