line 11892=>     Sing hey! for the bath at close of day 
line 11893=>     that washes the weary mud away! 
line 11894=>     A loon is he that will not sing: 
line 11895=>     O! Water Hot is a noble thing! 
line 11896=> 
line 11897=>     O! Sweet is the sound of falling rain, 
line 11898=>     and the brook that leaps from hill to plain; 
line 11899=>     but better than rain or rippling streams 
line 11900=>     is Water Hot that smokes and steams. 
line 11901=> 
line 11902=>     O! Water cold we may pour at need 
line 11903=>     down a thirsty throat and be glad indeed; 
line 11904=>     but better is Beer, if drink we lack, 
line 11905=>
line 11906=>####-     and Water Hot poured down the back. 
line 11907=> 
