line 11957=>     'Old Maggot is  a shrewd fellow,' said Merry. 'A lot goes on behind his 
line 11958=>round face that does not come out in his talk. I've heard that he used to go 
line 11959=>into the Old Forest at one time, and he has the reputation of knowing a good 
line 11960=>many  strange things. But you can at least tell us, Frodo, whether you think  
line 11961=>his guess good or bad.' 
line 11962=>     'I think,'  answered Frodo slowly, 'that it was a good guess, as  far as 
line 11963=>it  goes. There is a  connexion with Bilbo's  old adventures,  and the Riders 
line 11964=>are looking,  or perhaps one  ought to say  searching,  for him or for me. I 
