line 11989=>Sackville-Bagginses! And all those close talks with Gandalf.' 
line 11990=>     'Good  heavens!'  said Frodo. 'I thought  I had been  both  careful and 
line 11991=>clever. I don't know what Gandalf would say. Is all  the Shire discussing my  
line 11992=>departure then?' 
line 11993=>     'Oh no!' said Merry. 'Don't worry about that! The secret won't keep for  
line 11994=>long,  of  course;  but  at  present it  is,  I  think,  only  known  to  us 
line 11995=>conspirators. After  all, you must remember  that we know you  well, and are 
