line 12012=>     'My dear  and  most beloved hobbits!'  said Frodo deeply  moved. 'But I 
line 12013=>could not  allow it. I decided that  long ago, too. You speak of danger, but 
line 12014=>you do not understand. This is no treasure-hunt,  no there-and -back journey.  
line 12015=>I am flying from deadly peril into deadly peril.' 
line 12016=>     'Of course  we understand,'  said Merry  firmly.  'That is why we  have 
line 12017=>decided to come. We know the Ring is no laughing-matter; but we are going to 
line 12018=>do our best to help you against the Enemy.' 
line 12019=>
line 12020=>####-     'The Ring!' said Frodo, now completely amazed. 
line 12021=>     'Yes, the Ring,' said  Merry. 'My dear old hobbit, you don't  allow for  
line 12022=>the inquisitiveness of friends. I have known about the existence of the Ring 
line 12023=>for years  - before Bilbo went away, in fact; but since he obviously regarded 
line 12024=>it  as  secret,  I  kept  the  knowledge  in  my  head, until we formed  our 
line 12025=>conspiracy. I  did not know Bilbo, of course, as  well as I know you; I  was 
line 12026=>too young, and he was also more careful  - but  he was not careful enough. If 
line 12027=>you want to know how I first found out, I will tell you.' 
line 12028=>     'Go on!' said Frodo faintly. 
line 12029=>     'It was  the  Sackville-Bagginses that were his downfall,  as you might 
line 12030=>expect. One day, a year before the Party, I happened to be walking along the  
line 12031=>road, when I  saw Bilbo ahead. Suddenly in the distance the S.-B.s appeared, 
line 12032=>coming towards us.  Bilbo slowed down, and then hey presto! he  vanished.  I 
line 12033=>was so startled that I hardly had the wits to hide myself in a more ordinary 
line 12034=>fashion; but  I got through the hedge and walked along the  field inside.  I 
line 12035=>was  peeping  through into the road,  after the S.-B.s  had  passed, and was 
line 12036=>looking  straight at Bilbo  when he suddenly reappeared. I caught a glint of 
line 12037=>gold as he put something back in his trouser -pocket. 
line 12038=>     'After that I kept my  eyes open.  In fact, I confess that I spied. But 
line 12039=>you must  admit that it was very  intriguing, and I was only in my teens.  I 
