line 12044=>     'Not  too safe, I should say,' said  Merry.  'But  I have  only had one 
line 12045=>rapid glance, and that was difficult to get. He never left the book about. I 
line 12046=>wonder what became  of it. I should  like  another look.  Have you  got  it, 
line 12047=>Frodo?' 
line 12048=>     'No. It was not at Bag End. He must have taken it away.' 
line 12049=>     'Well, as  I  was saying,' Merry  proceeded, 'I  kept my  knowledge  to 
line 12050=>myself,  till  this Spring  when  things got  serious. Then  we  formed  our 
line 12051=>conspiracy;  and  as we were serious, too,  and meant business,  we have not  
