line 12765=>Chapter 7. In the House of Tom Bombadil 
line 12766=>
line 12767=> 
line 12768=> 
line 12769=>     The four hobbits stepped  over the  wide  stone  threshold,  and  stood 
line 12770=>still,  blinking. They  were in a  long  low room,  filled with the light of 
line 12771=>lamps swinging from the beams of the roof; and on the table of dark polished 
line 12772=>wood stood many candles, tall and yellow, burning brightly. 
line 12773=>     In a  chair, at the far side of the room  facing  the outer door, sat a  
line 12774=>woman. Her long yellow hair rippled down her shoulders;  her  gown was 
line 12775=>green, 
line 12776=>green as young reeds, shot  with silver like beads  of dew; and her belt was 
line 12777=>of gold, shaped like a chain  of flag-lilies set with the pale-blue  eyes of 
line 12778=>forget-me-nots.  About  her  feel  in  wide   vessels  of  green  and  brown 
