line 12792=>out  across  it. 'Let us  shut out the night!'  she said. 'For you are still 
line 12793=>afraid, per haps, of mist and tree-shadows and deep water, and untame things. 
line 12794=>Fear nothing! For tonight you are under the roof of Tom Bombadil.' 
line 12795=>     The hobbits looked at her in wonder; and she looked at each of them and  
