line 13072=>stone-rings  upon the  hills and in the hollows among the hills.  Sheep were 
line 13073=>bleating in flocks. Green  walls and white walls rose. There were fortresses 
line 13074=>on the heights. Kings of little kingdoms fought together, and the young  Sun 
line 13075=>shone like fire  on the red metal of their  new and greedy swords. There was 
line 13076=>victory and defeat; and towers fell, fortresses were burned, and flames went  
line 13077=>up into the sky. Gold was piled on the  biers of dead kings and queens;  and 
line 13078=>mounds covered them, and the stone  doors were shut; and the grass grew over  
line 13079=>all. Sheep  walked  for a while biting the  grass,  but soon the hills  were 
line 13080=>empty again.  A  shadow came out of dark places far away, and the bones were 
line 13081=>stirred in  the  mounds.  Barrow-wights walked in  the hollow places  with a  
