line 13084=>     The  hobbits   shuddered.   Even  in  the   Shire  the  rumour  of  the 
line 13085=>Barrow-wights of  the Barrow-downs beyond the Forest had  been heard. But it 
line 13086=>was not a tale that  any  hobbit  liked to listen  to, even by a comfortable 
line 13087=>fireside far away. These  four now  suddenly remembered what the joy of this 
line 13088=>house had  driven from their minds: the  house of Tom Bombadil nestled under 
