line 13095=>starlight, when only the Elf-sires were awake. Then suddenly he slopped, and 
line 13096=>they saw that he nodded  as if he was falling asleep.  The hobbits sat still 
line 13097=>before  him, enchanted; and it  seemed as if, under the  spell of his words, 
line 13098=>the wind  had gone, and the clouds had  dried  up,  and  the  day  had  been 
line 13099=>withdrawn, and darkness  had  come from  East and West, and all  the sky was 
line 13100=>filled with the light of white stars.  
line 13101=>     Whether the morning and evening of  one  day or of many days had passed 
line 13102=>Frodo could not tell.  He did not feel either hungry  or tired,  only filled 
line 13103=>with  wonder.  The  stars shone through the window and the  silence  of  the  
