line 13548=>     Tom stooped, removed his hat, and came into the dark chamber, singing:  
line 13549=>     Get out, you old Wight! Vanish in the sunlight! 
line 13550=>     Shrivel like the cold mist, like the winds go wailing, 
line 13551=>     Out into the barren lands far beyond the mountains! 
line 13552=>     Come never here again! Leave your barrow empty! 
line 13553=>     Lost and forgotten be, darker than the darkness, 
