line 13789=>     'There  are  hobbits in Bree,'  said Merry,  'as well as  Big  Folk.  I 
line 13790=>daresay it will be homelike  enough. The Pony is a good inn by all accounts.  
line 13791=>My people ride out there now and again.' 
line 13792=>     'It may be all we could wish,' said Frodo; 'but it is outside the Shire 
line 13793=>all the same. Don't  make yourselves  too much at home! Please remember -all 
line 13794=>of you - that the name of Baggins must NOT be mentioned. I am Mr. Underhill, 
line 13795=>if any name must be given.' 
line 13796=>     They now mounted  their ponies and rode off  silently into the evening. 
line 13797=>Darkness came down quickly,  as they  plodded slowly  downhill and up again, 
