line 13953=>streamed out of it. Above the arch  there was a lamp, and beneath it swung a  
line 13954=>large signboard: a  fat white pony reared up on  its hind legs. Over the door 
line 13955=>was painted in white letters: THE PRANCING PONY by BARLIMAN  
line 13956=>BUTTERBUR. Many 
line 13957=>of the lower windows showed lights behind thick curtains.  
line 13958=>
line 13959=>####-     As they hesitated outside in the gloom, someone began singing  a  merry 
line 13960=>song  inside, and many  cheerful voices  joined loudly in the  chorus.  They 
line 13961=>listened  to  this encouraging sound for a moment and  then  got  off  their 
