line 13963=>     They led their ponies under the arch, and leaving  them standing in the 
line 13964=>yard they climbed up  the steps. Frodo went forward and nearly bumped into a  
line 13965=>short fat man with a bald head and a red  face. He had a white apron on, and 
line 13966=>was  bustling out of  one door and in through another, carrying a tray laden 
line 13967=>with full mugs.  
line 13968=>     'Can we--' began Frodo. 
line 13969=>     'Half a minute, if  you please!' shouted the man over his shoulder, and 
line 13970=>vanished into a babel of voices and a cloud of smoke. In a moment he was out 
line 13971=>again, wiping his hands on his apron. 
line 13972=>     'Good  evening, little master!' he said, bending down. 'What may you be 
line 13973=>wanting?' 
line 13974=>     'Beds for four, and stabling for five ponies,  if that can be  managed. 
line 13975=>Are you Mr. Butterbur?' 
line 13976=>     'That's right! Barliman is my name. Barliman Butterbur at your service!  
