line 14054=>dwarves,  and other vague figures difficult to make out away  in the shadows 
line 14055=>and comers.  
line 14056=>     As soon as the Shire-hobbits  entered, there  was  a  chorus of welcome 
line 14057=>from the Bree-landers. The strangers, especially those that  had come up the 
line 14058=>Greenway, stared at them curiously. The landlord introduced the newcomers to 
line 14059=>the Bree-folk, so  quickly  that, though they caught  many  names, they were 
line 14060=>seldom  sure who the names belonged to.  The Men of Bree seemed  all to have 
line 14061=>rather  botanical (and to the Shire-folk rather odd) names,  like Rushlight, 
line 14062=>Goatleaf,  Heathertoes,  Appledore, Thistlewool and  Ferny (not  to  mention  
