line 15552=>     In hidden hollows quavering. 
line 15553=>     Now withered lay the hemlock-sheaves, 
line 15554=>     And one by one with sighing sound  
line 15555=>     Whispering fell the beechen leaves 
line 15556=>     In the wintry woodland wavering. 
line 15557=> 
line 15558=>     He sought her ever, wandering far 
line 15559=>     Where leaves of years were thickly strewn, 
line 15560=>     By light of moon and ray of star 
line 15561=>     In frosty heavens shivering. 
line 15562=>     Her mantle glinted in the moon, 
line 15563=>     As on a hill-top high and far 
line 15564=>     She danced, and at her feet was strewn  
line 15565=>
line 15566=>####-     A mist of silver quivering. 
line 15567=> 
line 15568=>     When winter passed, she came again, 
line 15569=>     And her song released the sudden spring, 
line 15570=>     Like rising lark, and falling rain, 
line 15571=>     And melting water bubbling. 
line 15572=>     He saw the elven-flowers spring 
line 15573=>     About her feet, and healed again  
line 15574=>     He longed by her to dance and sing 
line 15575=>     Upon the grass untroubling. 
line 15576=> 
line 15577=>     Again she fled, but swift he came. 
line 15578=>     TinÂ®viel! TinÂ®viel! 
line 15579=>     He called her by her elvish name; 
line 15580=>     And there she halted listening. 
line 15581=>     One moment stood she, and a spell 
line 15582=>     His voice laid on her: Beren came, 
