line 15965=>in  which he  walked on the grass in his garden in the Shire,  but it seemed 
line 15966=>faint  and dim, less clear  than the  tall black shadows that  stood looking 
line 15967=>over the hedge. 
line 15968=>     In  the morning he  woke to  find that the rain had stopped. The clouds 
line 15969=>were still thick,  but they were breaking, and pale strips of  blue appeared 
line 15970=>between them.  The  wind was  shifting  again.  They  did  not start  early.  
line 15971=>Immediately after  their cold  and  comfortless  breakfast Strider  went off 
line 15972=>alone, telling the others to remain under the shelter of the cliff, until he 
line 15973=>came  back. He was going to climb up, if he could, and get a look at the lie 
line 15974=>of the land. 
line 15975=>     When  he returned he was not reassuring.  'We have come too  far to the 
line 15976=>north,' he said, 'and we must find  some way to  turn back southwards again.  
