line 17000=>himself. When  he had left Hobbiton he had wandered off aimlessly, along the 
line 17001=>Road or in the country on either side;  but  somehow  he had steered all the 
line 17002=>time towards Rivendell. `I got here without  much adventure,' he  said, `and 
line 17003=>after  a rest I went on with  the dwarves to Dale: my last journey. I shan't  
line 17004=>travel again.  Old  Balin had gone away. Then I came  back  here, and here I  
line 17005=>have been. I have done this and that. I have  written some more of my  book. 
line 17006=>And, of course, I make  up a few songs. They sing them occasionally: just to 
line 17007=>please  me,  I think; for, of  course,  they aren't really  good  enough for  
line 17008=>Rivendell. And I listen and  I think. Time doesn't seem to pass here: it just  
line 17009=>is. A remarkable place altogether. 
line 17010=>     `I  hear  all kinds of  news,  from  over the Mountains, and out of the 
