line 17333=>     Next day Frodo woke  early, feeling refreshed and well. He walked along  
line 17334=>the terraces above  the  loud-flowing Bruinen and watched the pale, cool sun 
line 17335=>rise  above the far  mountains, and shine  down. Slanting  through the  thin 
line 17336=>silver mist;  the dew upon the  yellow leaves was glimmering, and  the woven 
line 17337=>nets of  gossamer twinkled  on  every bush.  Sam  walked beside  him, saying 
line 17338=>nothing.  but  sniffing the air, and looking every now and again with wonder  
line 17339=>in his eyes at the great heights in the East. The snow was white upon  their 
line 17340=>peaks. 
line 17341=>     On a seat cut  in  the  stone beside  a turn in the path they came upon 
line 17342=>Gandalf and  Bilbo  deep in  talk. `Hullo!  Good morning!' said Bilbo. `Feel  
line 17343=>ready for the  great council?' 
line 17344=>     `I feel ready  for anything,' answered Frodo. `But most of all I should 
line 17345=>like to go walking  today and  explore the valley. I should like to get into 
line 17346=>those pine-woods up there.' He pointed away far up the side of  Rivendell to  
line 17347=>the north. 
line 17348=>     'You may  have  a chance later,' said Gandalf. `But we cannot  make any 
line 17349=>plans yet. There is much to hear and decide today.' 
line 17350=>     Suddenly as they were talking a  single clear bell rang out.  `That  is 
line 17351=>the warning bell for the Council of Elrond,' cr ied Gandalf. `Come along now! 
line 17352=>Both you and Bilbo are wanted.' 
line 17353=>     Frodo and Bilbo followed the wizard quickly along the winding path back 
