line 17667=>Hold it up, and then Boromir will understand the remainder of his riddle.' 
line 17668=>     There was a hush, and all turned their eyes on Frodo. He was shaken  by 
line 17669=>a sudden shame and fear; and he felt a great reluctance to  reveal the Ring, 
line 17670=>
line 17671=>####-and a loathing of its touch. He wished he was far away. The Ring gleamed and 
line 17672=>flickered as he held it up before them in his trembling hand. 
line 17673=>     'Behold Isildur's Bane!' said Elrond. 
line 17674=>     Boromir's eyes glinted as he gazed at the golden thing. `The Halfling!' 
line 17675=>he  muttered.  `Is then the  doom of Minas Tirith come at last? But why then 
line 17676=>should we seek a broken sword?' 
line 17677=>     'The words were not the  doom of Minas Tir ith,' said Aragorn. `But doom 
