line 17687=>of  Elendil would be a help beyond  our hope-if  such a  thing could  indeed 
line 17688=>return out of  the  shadows  of  the past.' He look ed again  at Aragorn, and 
line 17689=>doubt was in his eyes. 
line 17690=>     Frodo felt Bilbo stir impatiently at his side. Evidently he was annoyed 
line 17691=>on his friend's behalf. Standing suddenly up he burst out: 
line 17692=>     All that is gold does not glitter, 
line 17693=>     Not all those who wander are lost; 
line 17694=>     The old that is strong does not wither, 
line 17695=>     Deep roots are not reached by the frost. 
line 17696=> 
line 17697=>     From the ashes a fire shall be woken, 
line 17698=>     A light from the shadows shall spring; 
line 17699=>     Renewed shall be blade that was broken: 
line 17700=>     The crownless again shall be king. 
line 17701=>     `Not very good perhaps, but to the point  -- if you need more beyond the 
