line 17999=>company. Smjagol, who is now called Gollum, has escaped.' 
line 18000=>     'Escaped?' cried Aragorn. 'That is ill news indeed. We shall all rue it 
line 18001=>bitterly, I fear. How came the folk of Thranduil to fail in their trust?' 
line 18002=>     `Not through lack of  watchfulness,' said Legolas; `but perhaps through 
line 18003=>over -kindliness. And we fear that the prisoner had aid from others, and that 
line 18004=>more is known of our doings than we could wish. We guarded this creature day 
line 18005=>and  night, at Gandalf's  bidding,  much  though we wearied of the task. But 
line 18006=>Gandalf  bade us  hope still for his cure, and we had not the  heart to keep  
line 18007=>him ever in dungeons under the earth, where he would fall  back into his old 
line 18008=>black thoughts.' 
line 18009=>     'You were less tender  to me,'  said Gluin with  a flash of his eyes as 
line 18010=>old memories were stirred  of  his imprisonment in  the  deep places of  the 
line 18011=>Elven-king's halls. 
line 18012=>
line 18013=>####-     'Now  come!' said Gandalf. `Pray do not interrupt, my good Gluin.  That 
line 18014=>was  a regrettable misunderstanding,  long set right. If  all the grievances 
line 18015=>that stand between Elves and  Dwarves are to  be brought up  here, we may as 
line 18016=>well abandon this Council.' 
line 18017=>     Gluin  rose and bowed, and Legolas  continued.  'In  the days  of  fair 
line 18018=>weather we led Gollum through the  woods; and there was a high tree standing 
line 18019=>alone far from the others which he liked to climb. Often we let him mount up 
line 18020=>to the highest branches, until he felt the free  wind; but we set a guard at 
line 18021=>the tree's foot. One day he refused to come down, and the guards had no mind 
line 18022=>to climb  after him: he had learned the trick of clinging to boughs with his 
line 18023=>feet as well as with his hands; so they sat by the tree far into the night. 
line 18024=>     'It was that very night of summer, yet moonless and starless, that Orcs 
line 18025=>came  on us at unawares. We drove them off after  some time;  they were many 
line 18026=>and  fierce, but they came from over  the mountains, and were unused  to the  
line 18027=>woods. When the battle was  over, we  found  that Gollum was  gone, and  his 
line 18028=>guards were slain  or taken. It then seemed plain to  us that the attack had 
line 18029=>been made for his rescue, and that he knew  of  it beforehand. How that  was 
line 18030=>contrived we cannot guess; but Gollum is cunning, and the spies of the Enemy 
line 18031=>are many. The dark things that were driven  out in  the year of the Dragon's 
line 18032=>fall have returned in greater  numbers, and Mirkwood is again an evil place,  
line 18033=>save where our realm is maintained. 
line 18034=>     `We have failed to  recapture Gollum.  We came on his trail among those 
line 18035=>of many Orcs, and it plunged deep into the Forest, going south. But ere long 
line 18036=>it escaped our  skill,  and  we  dared not  continue the hunt;  for we  were 
line 18037=>drawing nigh to Dol Guldur,  and that  is still a very evil place; we do not 
line 18038=>go that way.' 
line 18039=>     `Well,  well, he  is gone,' said Gandalf. 'We have no time  to seek for  
line 18040=>him again.  He must do what he will. But he may play a part yet that neither  
line 18041=>he nor Sauron have foreseen. 
line 18042=>     'And now  I will answer Galdor's other questions. What of Saruman? What 
line 18043=>are his counsels to us in this need? This tale I must tell in full, for only 
line 18044=>Elrond  has heard it yet, and that in brief, but it will bear on all that we 
line 18045=>must  resolve. It is the last  chapter in the Tale of the Ring, so far as it 
line 18046=>has yet gone. 
line 18047=>     'At the  end of June I was in the Shire, but a cloud of anxiety was  on 
line 18048=>my mind, and I rode to the southern borders of the little land; for I  had a  
line 18049=>foreboding  of some danger, still hidden  from  me but  drawing  near. There 
line 18050=>
line 18051=>####-messages reached me telling me of war and defeat in Gondor, and when I heard 
