line 18886=>     On the morning of the last day Frodo  was alone with Bilbo, and the old 
line 18887=>hobbit  pulled  out from under his bed a wooden box.  He lifted  the lid and 
line 18888=>fumbled inside. 
line 18889=>     'Here  is your sword,' he said. 'But it was broken, you know. I took it 
line 18890=>to  keep it safe but I've  forgotten to ask if the smiths  could mend it. No 
line 18891=>time now..  So I thought, perhaps,  you would care to have this,  don't  you  
