line 19329=>     'Very well,' said Gandalf. `But we must not  use the wood -- not unless 
line 19330=>it is a choice between fire and death.' 
line 19331=>     The Company set out again with good speed at first; but soon their  way 
line 19332=>became steep  and  difficult.  The twisting  and climbing road  had  in many  
line 19333=>places almost disappeared, and was  blocked  with  many fallen  stones.  The 
line 19334=>night grew deadly dark under great clouds. A  bitter wind swirled among  the 
line 19335=>rocks. By midnight they had climbed to the knees of the great mountains. The 
line 19336=>narrow path now wound  under a sheer wall of cliffs to the left, above which  
line 19337=>the grim flanks of Caradhras towered up invisible in the gloom; on the right  
