line 19371=>keep going. The hobbits, bent nearly double, toiled along behind  the taller 
line 19372=>folk, but it was  plain  that they could not  go much  further,  if the snow 
line 19373=>continued.  Frodo's  feet felt like lead. Pippin  was dragging behind.  Even 
line 19374=>Gimli, as stout as any dwarf could be, was grumbling as he trudged. 
