line 19704=>disaster in  the  snow, and have said no  word of  blame. I will follow your 
line 19705=>lead  now  -- if this last warning does not move you. It is  not of the Ring, 
line 19706=>nor of  us others that  I am thinking now, but of you, Gandalf. And I say to 
line 19707=>you: if you pass the doors of Moria, beware! ' 
line 19708=>     `I  will not go,' said Boromir;  'not  unless  the vote  of  the  whole 
line 19709=>company  is  against me.  What  do  Legolas and  the  little  folk  say? The 
line 19710=>
