line 19994=>     'Dwarf-doors are  not made to be seen when shut,' said Gimli. `They are 
line 19995=>invisible, and their own  masters cannot  find them or  open them,  if their 
line 19996=>secret is forgotten.' 
line 19997=>     'But this Door was not made to be a secret known only to Dwarves,' said 
line 19998=>Gandalf, coming  suddenly to  life and turning  round.  `Unless  things  are 
line 19999=>altogether changed, eyes that know what to look for may discover the signs.' 
line 20000=>     He walked forward  to the wall. Right  between the shadow  of the trees 
line 20001=>there  was a smooth space,  and over this he passed  his  hands to and  fro, 
