line 20457=>     There shone for ever fair and bright. 
line 20458=> 
line 20459=>     There hammer on the anvil smote, 
line 20460=>     There chisel clove, and graver wrote; 
line 20461=>     There forged was blade, and bound was hilt; 
line 20462=>     The delver mined, the mason built. 
line 20463=>     There beryl, pearl, and opal pale, 
line 20464=>     And metal wrought like fishes' mail, 
line 20465=>     Buckler and corslet, axe and sword, 
