line 20543=>near him, and that a  dim light  was falling on his face. High  up above the 
line 20544=>eastern  archway through a shaft near  the roof came  a long pale gleam; and 
line 20545=>across the hall  through  the  northern  arch light also glimmered faint and 
line 20546=>
line 20547=>####-distantly. 
line 20548=>     Frodo sat up. `Good morning!  ' said  Gandalf: `For morning it is again 
line 20549=>at last. I was right,  you see.  We  are high up on the east  side of Moria. 
line 20550=>Before today is over we ought to find the Great  Gates and see the waters of 
line 20551=>Mirrormere lying in the Dimrill Dale before us.' 
line 20552=>     'I shall be glad,' said Gimli. `I have looked on  Moria, and it is very 
line 20553=>great, but it has become dark and dreadful; and we have found no  sign  of my 
line 20554=>kindred. I doubt now that Balin ever came here.' 
line 20555=>     After they had breakfasted Gandalf decided to go on again at  once. `We 
line 20556=>are tired, but we shall rest better  when we are outside,' he said. `I think  
line 20557=>that none of us will wish to spend another night in Moria.' 
line 20558=>     `No indeed! '  said Boromir. `Which way shall we take?  Yonder eastward 
line 20559=>arch?  ' 
line 20560=>     'Maybe,' said  Gandalf. `But  I du not know yet exactly  where  we are. 
line 20561=>Unless I am quite astray, I guess that  we are above and to the north of the 
line 20562=>Great Gates; and it may not be easy to find the right road down to them. The 
line 20563=>eastern arch will probably prove to be the way that we must take; but before 
line 20564=>we make up our minds we ought to look about us. Let us go towards that light 
