line 20600=>     The Company  of the Ring stood silent beside the  tomb of  Balin. Frodo 
line 20601=>thought  of  Bilbo  and his long friendship with the  dwarf,  and of Balin's 
line 20602=>visit to the  Shire long  ago. In  that dusty  chamber  in the mountains  it 
line 20603=>seemed a thousand years ago and on the other side of the world. 
line 20604=>     At length they stirred and looked up, and began  to search for anything 
line 20605=>that would give them tidings of Balin's fate, or show what had become of his 
line 20606=>folk. There was another smaller door on the other side of the chamber, under  
line 20607=>the shaft.  By both the doors they could now see that many bones were lying, 
line 20608=>and among  them  were  broken swords and axe-heads,  and cloven  shields and 
line 20609=>helms. Some of the swords were crooked: orc-scimitars with blackened blades.  
line 20610=>     There were many recesses cut in the rock of the walls, and in them were 
line 20611=>large iron-bound chests  of  wood. All had  been  broken and plundered;  but 
line 20612=>beside the shattered lid of one there lay the remains of a book. It had been 
line 20613=>slashed  and stabbed and partly burned, and it was so stained with black and 
line 20614=>other  dark  marks like old blood that little of  it could be  read. Gandalf 
