line 21442=>bough, though  these  trees are of a kind strange to  me, save as  a name in 
line 21443=>
line 21444=>####-song.  Mellyrn  they are called, and are those that bear the yellow blossom, 
line 21445=>but I have never climbed in one. I will see now what is  their shape and way 
line 21446=>of growth.' 
line 21447=>     `Whatever  it may be,'  said Pippin,  `they  will be  marvellous  trees 
line 21448=>indeed if they can offer any rest at night, except to birds. I cannot  sleep 
line 21449=>on a perch! ' 
line 21450=>     'Then dig a hole in the  ground,' said Legolas, `if that  is more after 
line 21451=>the fashion of your kind. But  you  must dig swift and deep, if you  wish to 
line 21452=>hide from Orcs.' He sprang  lightly up from the ground  and  caught a branch 
line 21453=>that grew from the trunk high above his head. But even as he swung there for 
line 21454=>a moment, a voice spoke suddenly from the tree-shadows above him. 
line 21455=>     `Daro!'  it said in commanding tone, and Legolas dropped back to  earth 
line 21456=>in surprise and fear. He shrank against the bole of the tree. 
line 21457=>     'Stand still! ' he whispered to the others. `Do not move or speak! ' 
line 21458=>     There  was a sound  of soft laughter over their heads, and then another  
line 21459=>clear voice spoke in an  elven-tongue. Frodo could understand little of what 
line 21460=>was  said, for the speech that the  Silvan folk east of the  mountains  used 
line 21461=>among themselves was unlike that of the West. Legolas looked up and 
line 21462=>answered 
line 21463=>in the same language.* 
line 21464=>     `Who are they, and what do they say? ' asked Merry. 
line 21465=>     `They're Elves,' said Sam. `Can't  you hear their voices? ' 
line 21466=>     `Yes, they are Elves,'  said Legolas; `and they say that you breathe so 
line 21467=>loud that they could  shoot you in the dark.' Sam  hastily put his hand over 
line 21468=>his mouth.  'But they say also that  you need have  no fear. They have  been 
line 21469=>aware of us for a long while. They heard  my  voice across the Nimrodel, and 
line 21470=>knew that I  was one of their  Northern kindred, and therefore they did  not 
