line 21898=>     The  sun  was  sinking  behind  the  mountains,  and the  shadows  were 
line 21899=>deepening in the woods, when  they went on again.  Their paths now went into 
line 21900=>thickets  where  the dusk had already gathered. Night came beneath the trees 
line 21901=>as they walked, and the Elves uncovered their silver lamps.  
line 21902=>     Suddenly they came out into the open again and found themselves under a 
line 21903=>pale evening sky pricked by a  few early  stars.  There  was a wide treeless 
line 21904=>space  before  them, running in a  great circle  and bending  away on  either  
line 21905=>hand. Beyond it was a deep fosse lost in soft shadow, but the grass upon its 
line 21906=>brink was green, as if it  glowed still in memory of the sun that  had gone. 
line 21907=>Upon the further side there rose to a great height a green wall encircling a  
line 21908=>green hill thronged with mallorn-trees taller than any they had yet seen  in 
line 21909=>all the land. Their height  could not be  guessed,  but they stood up in the 
line 21910=>twilight like living towers. In  their, many-tiered branches and amid  their 
line 21911=>ever -moving  leaves  countless  lights were  gleaming,  green and  gold  and  
line 21912=>silver. Haldir turned towards the Company. 
line 21913=>     `Welcome to  Caras  Galadhon!  ' he  said. 'Here  is the  city  of  the 
line 21914=>Galadhrim where dwell  the Lord Celeborn  and Galadriel  the Lady of Lurien. 
line 21915=>But we  cannot enter here,  for  the gates do not look northward. We must go  
line 21916=>round to the  southern side,  and the  way is  not  short,  for the city  is 
line 21917=>great.' 
line 21918=>     There was a road  paved with white stone  running on the outer brink of 
