line 22092=>     `What  did you  blush for, Sam?  ' said  Pippin. `You soon  broke down. 
line 22093=>Anyone would have thought you had a guilty conscience. I hope it was nothing 
line 22094=>worse than a wicked plot to steal one of my blankets.' 
line 22095=>     `I never thought no such thing,' answered Sam, in no mood for jest. 'If 
line 22096=>you  want to know, I felt as if I hadn't  got nothing on,  and I didn't like 
line 22097=>it. She seemed to be looking inside  me and asking me what I would do if she 
line 22098=>gave me the chance of  flying back home to the Shire to a nice  little  hole 
line 22099=>with-with a bit of garden of my own.' 
line 22100=>     `That's funny,' said Merry. 'Almost  exactly what I felt  myself; only, 
