line 23652=>     Frodo sat for a moment with his head bowed. Sam, who had  been watching 
line 23653=>his master with  great  concern, shook his  head and  muttered:  'Plain as a  
line 23654=>pikestaff it is, but it's no good Sam Gamgee putting in his spoke just now.' 
line 23655=>, 
line 23656=>     Presently Frodo  got  up and  walked away;  and Sam saw that  while the  
line 23657=>others restrained  themselves and did not stare at him,  the eyes of Boromir 
