line 23681=>     `I was afraid for  you, Frodo,' he said, coming forward. `If Aragorn is 
line 23682=>right and Orcs are near,  then none of us should wander alone, and you least  
line 23683=>of all: so much depends on you. And my heart too  is heavy. May  I  stay now 
line 23684=>and talk for a  while,  since  I have found  you? It would comfort me. Where 
line 23685=>there are so many, all speech becomes a debate without end. But two together  
line 23686=>may perhaps find wisdom.' 
line 23687=>     `You are kind,'  answered Frodo. 'But  I do not think  that  any speech 
line 23688=>will help me.  For  I know what I should do, but I  am  afraid of doing  it, 
