line 25203=>     'I will come,' said Aragorn. 
line 25204=>     'And I will come, too,' said Gimli. 'The matter  of the  Lady Galadriel 
line 25205=>lies still between us. I have yet to teach you gentle speech. ' 
line 25206=>     'We  shall see,' said Jomer. 'So many strange things  have chanced that 
line 25207=>to learn the praise of a fair lady under the loving strokes of a Dwarf's axe 
line 25208=>will seem no great wonder. Farewell!' 
line 25209=>     With that they parted.  Very swift were the horses of Rohan. When aft er 
