line 25219=>     'There  is  little  to  discover,'  he said when he returned. 'The main 
line 25220=>trail is all confused with the passage of  the  horsemen  as they came back; 
line 25221=>their outward  course  must have lain nearer  the river. But  this  eastward 
line 25222=>trail is fresh and clear. There is no sign there of any feet going the other  
line 25223=>way, back towards  Anduin. Now  we  must ride slower, and make sure  that no 
line 25224=>trace or footstep branches off on either side. The Orcs must have been aware 
line 25225=>from this point that they were  pursued; they may have made some  attempt to 
line 25226=>get their captives away before they were overtaken.' 
line 25227=>     As they rode forward the  day  was overcast.  Low grey clouds came over  
line 25228=>the  Wold.  A  mist  shrouded the sun. Ever nearer  the  tree-clad slopes of 
line 25229=>
