line 25838=>into thick cloud, and  Pippin could not  see anything  a few feet away.  The 
line 25839=>fires brought no light to the hillock. The riders were not, however, content 
line 25840=>merely to wait  for  the dawn and let their enemies rest. A sudden outcry on 
line 25841=>the  east side of the  knoll showed that something was wrong. It seemed that 
line 25842=>some of the Men  had ridden in  close, slipped  off their horses, crawled to 
line 25843=>the edge of the camp and killed several Orcs, and then had faded away again. 
line 25844=>UglÂ®k dashed off to stop a stampede. 
line 25845=>     Pippin  and  Merry sat up.  Their guards,  Isengarders,  had  gone with 
