line 26599=>     'Good! Good!'  said  Treebeard. 'But I spoke   hastily. We must  not  be 
line 26600=>hasty. I have become too hot. I must cool myself and think; fur it is easier 
line 26601=>to shout stop! than to do it.' 
line 26602=>     He strode to the archway and stood for some time under the falling rain 
line 26603=>of the spring. Then he laughed and shook himself, and wherever the  drops of 
line 26604=>water fell glittering from him to the ground they glinted like red and green 
