line 26676=>fair she was still in my eyes, when I had last seen her, though  little like 
line 26677=>the  Entmaiden  of old.  For  the Entwives were bent  and  browned  by their  
line 26678=>labour; their hair  parched  by the sun to the hue  of ripe corn  and  their 
