line 26682=>Entwives were not there. Long  we called, and long we searched; and we asked 
line 26683=>all  folk  that  we  met which way the Entwives had gone. Some said they had 
line 26684=>never seen them;  and  some said that they had seen them walking  away west, 
line 26685=>and some said east, and others south. But nowhere that we went could we find 
line 26686=>them. Our sorrow was very great. Yet the wild  wood called, and we  returned 
line 26687=>to it. For many years we used to go out every now and again and look for the 
line 26688=>Entwives.  walking far and wide and  calling  them by their beautiful names.  
