line 26766=>     They  woke to find a cool sun  shining into the great court, and on  to 
line 26767=>the floor of the bay. Shreds of high cloud were overhead, running on a stiff 
line 26768=>
line 26769=>####-easterly wind. Treebeard was not to be seen; but while Merry and Pippin were 
line 26770=>bathing in the basin by the arch, they heard him humming and  singing, as he 
line 26771=>came up the path between the trees.  
line 26772=>     'Hoo, ho! Good morning, Merry and Pippin!' he boomed, when he saw 
line 26773=>them. 
line 26774=>'You  sleep long. I have  been many a hundred  strides already today. Now we 
line 26775=>will have a drink, and go to Entmoot.' 
line 26776=>     He  poured  them  out two  full bowls  from a  stone  jar;  but  from a  
