line 26786=>have  managed  to make a fair number  promise to come.  We shall meet in the 
line 26787=>place  where we have always met: Derndingle  Men  call it.  It is away south 
line 26788=>from here. We must be there before noon.' 
line 26789=>     Before long they set off. Treebeard carried the  hobbits in his arms as 
line 26790=>on the previous day. At  the entrance to  the court he turned  to the right, 
line 26791=>stepped over the stream, and strode away southwards along  the feet of great 
line 26792=>tumbled slopes where trees were scanty. Above these the hobbits saw thickets 
