line 27011=>stars. 
line 27012=>     The third day broke, bleak and windy.   At sunrise the Ents' voices rose 
line 27013=>to a great clamour and then died down again. As the morning wore on the wind 
line 27014=>fell  and  the  air grew  heavy with expectancy. The hobbits could  see that 
line 27015=>Bregalad  was now listening intently, although to them,  down in the dell of 
line 27016=>his ent-house, the sound of the Moot was faint. 
line 27017=>     The afternoon came, and the sun, going west towards the mountains. sent 
line 27018=>out  long  yellow beams  between the  cracks  and  fissures of  the  clouds.  
