line 27021=>that mean? Bregalad was standing up erect and tense, looking back northwards 
line 27022=>towards Derndingle. 
line 27023=>     Then with  a crash came  a great ringing shou t:  ra-hoom-rah! The trees 
line 27024=>quivered and bent as if a gust had struck them. There was another pause, and 
line 27025=>then a  marching  music began like solemn drums, and above the rolling beats 
line 27026=>and booms there welled voices singing high and strong. 
line 27027=>     We come, we come with roll of drum: ta -runda runda runda rom! 
line 27028=>     The Ents were coming: ever nearer and louder rose their song: 
line 27029=>     We come, we come with horn and drum: ta -ryna ryna ryna rom! 
line 27030=>     Bregalad picked up the hobbits and strode from his house. 
line 27031=>     Before  long  they  saw the  marching  line approaching: the Ents  were 
line 27032=>swinging along with great strides down the slope towards them. Treebeard was 
line 27033=>at  their head,  and  some  fifty followers  were  behind him,  two abreast, 
line 27034=>
line 27035=>####-keeping step with their feet  and beating time  with  their hands upon their 
