line 27039=>Moot! We are off. We are off to Isengard!' 
line 27040=>     'To Isengard!' the Ents cried in many voices.  
line 27041=>     'To Isengard!' 
line 27042=>     To Isengard! Though Isengard be ringed and barred with doors of stone; 
line 27043=>     Though Isengard be strong and hard, as cold as stone and bare as bone, 
line 27044=>     We go, we go, we go to war, to hew the stone and break the door; 
line 27045=>     For bole and bough are burning now, the furnace roars -- we go to war! 
line 27046=>     To land of gloom with tramp  of doom, with  roll  of drum, we come,  we  
line 27047=>come; 
line 27048=>     To Isengard with doom we come! 
line 27049=>     With doom we come, with doom we come! 
line 27050=>     So they sang as they marched southwards. 
line 27051=>     Bregalad, his eyes shining, swung into  the  line beside Treebeard. The 
