line 28516=>     'But  when I escaped and  warned you, then the mask was torn, for those 
line 28517=>who would see. After  that Wormtongue played dangerously, always  seeking 
line 28518=>to 
line 28519=>delay  you, to  prevent  your full strength being gathered.  He  was crafty: 
line 28520=>dulling men's  wariness, or working on their fears,  as served the occasion. 
line 28521=>Do you not remember how eagerly  he urged  that no man should be spared on 
line 28522=>a 
line 28523=>wildgoose  chase  northward,  when  the  immediate  peril was  westward?  He 
