line 28618=>     'A safer seat than many, I guess,' said Legolas. 'Yet doubtless Gandalf 
line 28619=>will  gladly put you  down  on  your  feet  when  blows  begin; or Shadowfax 
line 28620=>himself. An axe is no weapon for a rider.' 
line 28621=>     'And a Dwarf is no horseman. It is orc-necks I would hew, not shave the 
line 28622=>scalps of Men,' said Gimli, patting the haft of his axe. 
line 28623=>     At the gate they found a great host of men, old and young, all ready in 
