line 28777=>who  had  made  his refuge there. Ever steeper and narrower it wound  inward 
line 28778=>from  the  north  under the shadow  of the Thrihyrne, till the  crow-haunted 
line 28779=>cliffs rose  like mighty towers on either side, shutting out the light. 
line 28780=>     At Helm's Gate, before the  mouth of the Deep, there was a heel of rock  
line 28781=>thrust outward by the northern cliff. There  upon its spur stood  high walls 
line 28782=>of  ancient stone, and within them was a lofty  tower. Men said that  in the 
line 28783=>far-off  days of  the glory  of  Gondor  the  sea -kings  had built here this 
line 28784=>fastness with the hands of giants. The Hornburg it was called, for a trumpet 
line 28785=>sounded  upon   the   tower  echoed  in  the  Deep  behind,  as   i f  armies 
line 28786=>
line 28787=>####-long-forgotten  were issuing to war from  caves beneath the  hills. A  wall, 
line 28788=>too,  the men  of old  had made  from the  Hornburg to  the  southern cliff,  
