line 28820=>     'It is very great,' said the scout. 'He  that flies counts every foeman 
line 28821=>twice, yet I have spoken  to stouthearted  men, and I do not doubt that  the 
line 28822=>main strength of the enemy is many times as great as all that we have here.' 
line 28823=>     'Then let us be swift,' said Jomer. 'Let us drive through such foes  as 
line 28824=>
line 28825=>####-are  already  between  us  and the  fastness. There are caves in Helm's Deep 
line 28826=>where hundreds may lie hid; and secret ways lead thence up on to the hills.  
line 28827=>     'Trust not to secret ways,' said the king. 'Saruman  has long spied out 
line 28828=>this land. Still in that place our defence may last long. Let us go!' 
line 28829=>     Aragorn and  Legolas went now with Jomer in the van. On through the dark 
line 28830=>night they rode, ever  slower as the darkness deepened and their way climbed 
line 28831=>southward, higher and higher into the  dim folds about the  mountains' feet. 
line 28832=>They  found  few of the  enemy before  them. Here and  there they came  upon 
line 28833=>roving bands of Orcs; but they fled ere the Riders could take or slay them. 
line 28834=>     'It will not be long I fear,' said Jomer, 'ere the coming of the king's 
line 28835=>host will be known to the leader of our enemies, Saruman or whatever captain 
line 28836=>he has sent forth.' 
line 28837=>     The rumour of war grew behind them. Now they could hear, borne over the 
line 28838=>dark,  the  sound  of harsh  singing.  They  had  climbed far  up  into  the 
line 28839=>Deeping-coomb  when they looked back. Then they saw torches countless 
line 28840=>points 
line 28841=>of fiery light upon the  black fields behind, scattered like red flowers, or  
