line 28850=>     'We need not  fly much further,' said Jomer.  'Not  far ahead now  lies 
line 28851=>Helm's  Dike,  an  ancient trench  and rampart scored across the  coomb, two 
line 28852=>furlongs below Helm's Gate. There we can turn and give ba ttle.' 
line 28853=>     'Nay, we are too  few to defend the Dike,' said Thjoden. 'It  is a mile 
line 28854=>long or more, and the breach in it is wide.' 
line 28855=>     'At  the breach our  rearguard  must  stand,  if we  are pressed,' said 
line 28856=>Jomer. 
line 28857=>     There was neither star  nor moon when  the Riders came  to the breach in  
line 28858=>the Dike, where the stream from above passed out, and the road beside it ran 
line 28859=>down from  the  Hornburg. The  rampart loomed suddenly  before  them, a high 
line 28860=>shadow beyond a dark pit. As they rode up a sentinel challenged them. 
line 28861=>     'The Lord of the Mark rides  to Helm's Gate,' Jomer answered. 'I, Jomer  
line 28862=>
