line 29398=>     'My  men  are weary with battle,' said the King; 'and  I am weary also. 
line 29399=>For I have ridden far and slept little. Alas! My  old age is not feigned nor  
line 29400=>due only to the  whisperings  of  Wormtongue. It is an ill that no leech can 
line 29401=>wholly cure, not even Gandalf.' 
line 29402=>     'Then let all who are to ride with me rest now,' said Gandalf. 'We will 
