line 29415=>Gandalf 
line 29416=>would go  Aragorn, and Legolas, and Gimli. In spite  of his hurt  the  dwarf 
line 29417=>would not stay behind. 
line 29418=>     'It  was only a  feeble blow and the cap turned it;' he said. 'It would 
line 29419=>take more than such an orc-scratch to keep me back.' 
line 29420=>     'I will tend it, while you rest,' said Aragorn. 
line 29421=>     The king now returned to the Hornburg, and slept, such a sleep of quie t 
