line 29434=>of  you  have got  death  as  the  reward  of your trust in him; but had you  
line 29435=>conquered, little better would your wages have been.' 
line 29436=>     The men of Dunland were amazed, for Saruman had told  them that the men 
line 29437=>of Rohan were cruel and burned their captives alive. 
line 29438=>     In the  midst of  the field before the Hornburg two mounds were raised, 
line 29439=>and  beneath them  were laid  all  the Riders of the Mark who  fell  in  the 
line 29440=>defence, those of the  East Dales upon one side, and  those of Westfold upon  
