line 30213=>     'Though Isengard be strong and hard, as cold as stone and bare as bone, 
line 30214=>     We go, we go, we go to war, to hew the stone and break the door! 
line 30215=>     There was  very much more. A  great deal  of the song had no words, and  
line 30216=>was like a music of horns and drums.  It was very exciting. But I thought it 
line 30217=>was only marching music and no more, just a song  -- until I got here. I know 
line 30218=>better now.' 
line 30219=>     'We came down  over  the last  ridge  into Nan Curunnr, after night had 
