line 30295=>don't like axes. But there would have to be a great many axe -men to one Ent: 
line 30296=>a man  that hacks once at  an  Ent  never  gets a chance of a second blow. A 
line 30297=>punch from an Ent-fist crumples up iron like thin tin. 
line 30298=>     'When Treebeard had got a few  arrows  in  him, he began to warm up, to  
