line 30893=>into  the  tower, to discuss  deep  things beyond their comprehension in the 
line 30894=>high chambers of  Orthanc. The door would be closed, and they would  be left  
line 30895=>outside, dismissed to await allotted work or punishment. Even in the mind of 
line 30896=>Thjoden the thought took shape, like a shadow of doubt: 'He will betray  us;  
line 30897=>he will go -- we shall be lost.' 
line 30898=>     Then Gandalf laughed. The fantasy vanished like a puff of smoke. 
