line 31618=>stride of Shadowfax bears you nearer to the Land of Shadow, Peregrin Took.' 
line 31619=>     Pippin made no answer, but clutched his cloak, as if a sudden chill had 
line 31620=>struck him. Grey land passed under them. 
line 31621=>     'See now!' said Gandalf. 'The Westfold dales  are  opening  before  us.  
line 31622=>Here we come back to the eastward  road. The dark shadow yonder is the 
line 31623=>mouth 
line 31624=>of the  Deeping-coomb. That way lies Aglarond a nd the  Glittering Caves.  Do 
