line 31763=>and more  frequent, Frodo  and Sam were driven to their left, well away from 
line 31764=>the edge, and they did not notice that for several miles they had been going 
line 31765=>slowly but steadily downhill: the cliff-top was sinking towards the level of 
line 31766=>the lowlands. 
line 31767=>     At last  they were brought to a  halt.  The ridge took  a  sharper bend 
line 31768=>nor thward and was gashed by  a deeper  ravine. On the further side it reared 
line 31769=>up again,  many fathoms at a single  leap: a great grey cliff  loomed before 
line 31770=>them, cut sheer down  as if by  a  knife stroke.  They could  go  no further 
line 31771=>forwards, and must turn now either west or east. But west  would  lead  them 
line 31772=>only  into more labour and delay, back towards the  heart of the hills; east 
line 31773=>
line 31774=>####-would take them to the outer precipice. 
line 31775=>     `There's nothing for it but  to scramble down  this gully,  Sam,'  said 
line 31776=>Frodo. `Let's see what it leads to!' 
line 31777=>     'A nasty drop, I'll bet,' said Sam. 
line 31778=>     The  cleft  was  longer and deeper  than it seemed. Some way down  they 
line 31779=>found a  few gnarled and stunted  trees,  the first they  had seen for days: 
line 31780=>twisted birch for  the  most part, with here and there a fir -tree. Many were 
line 31781=>dead and gaunt, bitten to the core by the eastern winds. Once in milder days 
line 31782=>there must have been a fair thicket in the ravine, but now, after some fifty 
line 31783=>yards,  the  trees  came to  an end, though  old broken stumps  straggled on 
line 31784=>almost to the cliff's brink. The bottom of  the  gully, which  lay along the 
line 31785=>edge of a rock -fault, was rough with broken stone and slanted steeply  down. 
line 31786=>When they came at last to the end of it, Frodo stooped and leaned out. 
line 31787=>     `Look!' he said. `We must have come down a  long way, or else the cliff 
line 31788=>has sunk. It's much lower here than it was, and it looks easier too.' 
line 31789=>     Sam knelt beside  him  and peered  reluctantly over the  edge.  Then he 
