line 31879=>     There  was another crack  of  thunder;  and then  the  rain came.  In a  
line 31880=>blinding sheet, mingled with hail, it drove against the cliff, bitter cold. 
line 31881=>     'I'm  coming  down to you,' shouted Sam, though how he hoped to help in 
line 31882=>that way he could not have said. 
line 31883=>     `No,  no!  wait!  ' Frodo  called back, more strongly now. `I  shall be 
line 31884=>better  soon. I feel  better already. Wait! You can't do anything  without a  
line 31885=>rope.' 
line 31886=>     `Rope!'  cried  Sam, talking wildly to himself  in  his  excitement and 
line 31887=>
line 31888=>####-relief. `Well, if I don't deserve  to be hung on the end of one as a warning 
line 31889=>to numbskulls!  You're nowt  but a ninnyhammer, Sam Gamgee: that's  what 
line 31890=>the 
line 31891=>Gaffer said to me often enough, it being a word of his. Rope!' 
line 31892=>     `Stop  chattering!' cried  Frodo,  now  recovered  enough to feel  both 
