line 31894=>you've got some rope in your pocket? If so, out with it! 
line 31895=>     `Yes, Mr. Frodo, in my pack and  all.  Carried it hundreds of miles and 
line 31896=>I'd clean forgotten it!' 
line 31897=>     `Then get busy and let an end down!' 
line 31898=>     Quickly  Sam  unslung  his pack and rummaged in it. There indeed at the 
line 31899=>bottom was a coil  of the silken-grey rope made by the folk  of  Lurien.  He 
