line 32211=>guessed,' he  whispered;  `and we didn't  want  them  to  go,  did  we?  No, 
line 32212=>precious, not the nice hobbits. Ashes, ashes, and dust, and thirst there is;  
line 32213=>and pits, pits, pits, and Orcs, thousands of Orcses. Nice hobbits mustn't go 
line 32214=>to -- sss  -- those places.' 
line 32215=>     `So you have been there?  ' Frodo insisted. `And you're being drawn back  
line 32216=>there, aren't you?' 
line 32217=>     `Yess. Yess. No! ' shrieked Gollum. `Once, by  accident it  was, wasn't  
line 32218=>it, precious? Yes, by accident. But we won't go back, no, no!' Then suddenly  
line 32219=>his voice and language changed,  and he sobbed in his throat,  and spoke but 
line 32220=>not to them. `Leave me alone, gollum! You hurt me.  O my poor hands, gollum! 
line 32221=>I,  we, I don't want  to come back. I can't find it. I am tired. I, we can't  
line 32222=>find it, gollum, gollum,  no, nowhere. They 're always awake.  Dwarves,  Men, 
line 32223=>and Elves, terrible Elves  with  bright eyes. I can't find it. Ach! ' He got 
line 32224=>up and clenched his long hand into a bony fleshless knot, shaking it towards 
line 32225=>the East. 'We  won't! ' he  cried. 'Not for  you.' Then he collapsed   again. 
line 32226=>'Gollum, gollum,' he whimpered with his face  to the  ground. 'Don't look at 
line 32227=>us! Go away! Go to sleep!' 
line 32228=>     `He will not go  away or go to sleep at  your  command, Smjagol,'  said 
line 32229=>
line 32230=>####-Frodo. `But if you  really wish to be free of  him again. then you  must help 
line 32231=>me. And that I fear means finding us a path towards him. But you need not go 
line 32232=>all the way, not beyond the gates of his land.' 
line 32233=>     Gollum sat up  again  and looked at him under  his eyelids. 'He's  over  
line 32234=>there,' he cackled. `Always there. Orcs  wi ll take you all the  way. Easy to 
line 32235=>find Orcs east of  the River. Don't ask Smjagol. Poor, poor Smjagol, he went  
line 32236=>away long ago. They took his Precious, and he's lost now.' 
line 32237=>     `Perhaps we'll find him again, if you come with us,' said Frodo. 
line 32238=>     'No, no, never! He's lost his Precious,' said Gollum. 
line 32239=>     'Get up! ' said Frodo. 
line 32240=>     Gollum stood up and backed away against the cliff. 
line 32241=>     `Now! '  said Frodo. 'Can  you find  a path easier by day or by  night?  
line 32242=>We're tired; but if you choose the night, we'll star t tonight.' 
line 32243=>     `The big lights hurt our eyes, they do,' Gollum whined. `Not  under the 
line 32244=>White  Face, not  yet. It will go behind  the  hills soon, yess. Rest  a bit 
line 32245=>first, nice hobbits!' 
line 32246=>     `Then sit down,' said Frodo, `and don't move!' 
line 32247=>     The  hobbits  seated themselves  beside  him, one on  either side. with 
line 32248=>their backs to the stony wall, resting their legs. There was no need for any 
line 32249=>arrangement by word: they knew that they must not sleep for a moment. Slowly 
line 32250=>the moon went by. Shadows fell down from the hills, and all grew dark before 
line 32251=>them. The stars grew thick  and bright in  the sky  above.  No one  stirred. 
line 32252=>Gollum  sat  with his legs drawn up, knees  under chin, flat hands  and feet 
line 32253=>splayed on the ground,  his eyes closed; but he seemed tense, as if thinking 
line 32254=>or listening. 
line 32255=>     Frodo looked across at Sam. Their eyes met and  they  understood.  They 
line 32256=>relaxed,  leaning  their heads back, and  shutting their eyes or seeming to. 
line 32257=>Soon  the sound of  their  soft  breathing  could be  heard. Gollum's  hands 
line 32258=>twitched  a little. Hardly perceptibly his head moved  to  the left  and the 
line 32259=>right, and  first one eye and then the other opened a slit. The hobbits made 
line 32260=>no sign. 
line 32261=>     Suddenly,  with startling agility and  speed, straight  off  the ground 
line 32262=>with a jump like a  grasshopper or a frog. Gollum  bounded  forward into the  
line 32263=>darkness. But that was just what Frodo and Sam had expected.  Sam was on 
line 32264=>him 
line 32265=>before he had gone two paces after  his spring. Frodo coming behind  grabbed 
line 32266=>his leg and threw him. 
line 32267=>
line 32268=>####-     'Your rope might prove useful again, Sam.' he said. 
line 32269=>     Sam  got  out the  rope. 'And  where were you  off  to in the cold hard 
line 32270=>lands, Mr. Gollum?' he growled. 'We wonders.  aye,  we wonders. To find 
line 32271=>some 
line 32272=>of  your orc-friends,  I warrant. You nasty treacherous creature. It's round 
line 32273=>your neck this rope ought to go, and a tight noose too.' 
line 32274=>     Gollum lay quiet and tried  no further tricks.  He did not  answer Sam, 
line 32275=>but gave him a swift venomous look. 
line 32276=>     `All we need is something to keep a hold on him,' said Frodo. 'We  want 
line 32277=>him  to walk, so it's  no good  tying his legs-or his arms. he seems to  use 
line 32278=>them nearly as much. Tie one end to his  ankle, and keep a grip on the other  
line 32279=>end.' 
line 32280=>     He  stood over Gollum, while Sam  tied the  knot. The  result surprised 
line 32281=>them both. Gollum  began to scream, a thin, tearing sound, very  horrible to 
line 32282=>hear. He writhed, and tried to get his mouth to his ankle and bite the rope.  
line 32283=>He kept on screaming. 
line 32284=>     At last Frodo was  convinced that  he really was  in pain; but it could 
line 32285=>not be from the knot. He examined it  and found that  it was not too  tight, 
line 32286=>indeed  hardly  tight  enough. Sam was gentler than his words.  'What's  the 
line 32287=>matter with you? ' he said. `If you will try to run away. you must  be tied;  
line 32288=>but we don't wish to hurt you.' 
line 32289=>     'It hurts us, it hurts us,' hissed Gollum. `It freezes, it bites! Elves 
line 32290=>twisted it,  curse them! Nasty cruel hobbits! That's why we tries to escape, 
line 32291=>of course  it is, precious.  We guessed they were cruel hobbits. They visits 
line 32292=>Elves, fierce Elves with bright eyes. Take it off us! It hurts us.' 
line 32293=>     `No, I will not take it off you,' said Frodo, `not unless' -- he paused 
line 32294=>a  moment in thought -- `not unless there is any promise you can make that I  
line 32295=>can trust.' 
line 32296=>     'We  will swear to  do what he wants,  yes, yess,  said  Gollum,  still 
line 32297=>twisting and grabbling at his ankle. `It hurts us.' 
line 32298=>     `Swear? ' said Frodo. 
