line 32457=>said. `Leaves out of the elf-country,  gah! They stinks. He climbed in those 
line 32458=>trees,  and  he  couldn't  wash  the  smell  off  his hands, my nice hands.' 
line 32459=>Dropping the leaf, he took a corner of the   lembas  and nibbled it. He spat, 
line 32460=>and a fit  of coughing shook him. 
line 32461=>     `Ach! No!  '  he spluttered. `You try to  choke poor Smjagol.  Dust and 
line 32462=>ashes, he can't eat that. He must  starve. But  Smjagol  doesn't  mind. Nice 
line 32463=>hobbits! Smjagol has promised.  He will  starve. He can't eat hobbits' food. 
line 32464=>He will starve. Poor thin Smjagol! ' 
line 32465=>     `I'm sorry,' said Frodo; `but I can't help  you, I'm  afraid.  I  think  
line 32466=>this  food would do you good, if  you would try. But perhaps  you can't even  
line 32467=>try, not yet anyway.' 
line 32468=>     The hobbits munched their  lembas in silence. Sam thought that it tasted 
line 32469=>far better, somehow, than  it had for a  good while: Gollum's behaviour  had 
line 32470=>made him  attend to its flavour  again.  But  he did  not  feel comfortable. 
line 32471=>Gollum  watched every morsel from  hand to mouth, like an expectant dog by a  
