line 32631=>scraped on its surfaces by the faint quiver of empty seed-plumes, and broken  
line 32632=>grass-blades trembling in small air -movements that they could not feel. 
line 32633=>     'Not a bird! ' said Sam mournfully. 
line 32634=>     `No, no birds,' said  Gollum.  `Nice birds! ' He licked his  teeth. 'No 
line 32635=>birds  here.  There  are snakeses,  wormses,  things in the  pools. Lots  of 
line 32636=>things,  lots  of nasty things. No birds,' he ended sadly. Sam looked at him 
