line 32638=>     So passed  the  third day  of  their  journey with  Gollum.  Before the 
line 32639=>shadows of evening were long in happier lands, they went on again, always on 
line 32640=>and  on with only brief halts. These  they made not  so much for rest as  to 
line 32641=>help Gollum;  for now  even he had to go forward with great care, and he was 
line 32642=>sometimes at a loss for a while. They had come to the very midst of the Dead 
line 32643=>Marshes, and it was dark. 
line 32644=>     They  walked   slowly,  stooping,  keeping  close  in  line,  following 
line 32645=>attentively  every move that  Gollum made.  The fens grew more  wet, opening 
line 32646=>into  wide stagnant meres, among which it grew  more and more  difficult  to 
line 32647=>find the firmer places where feet could tread without sinking  into gurgling 
line 32648=>mud. The travellers were  light, or maybe none of them would ever have found 
line 32649=>a way through. 
line 32650=>     Presently it  grew  altogether  dark: the air  itself seemed  black and 
line 32651=>heavy to breathe. When lights appeared Sam  rubbed his eyes: he  thought his 
line 32652=>head was going  queer. He first  saw one with the corner of his  left eye, a  
