line 32657=>     At  last  Sam could bear it  no longer. `What's all this, Gollum? '  he 
line 32658=>said in a whisper. `These lights? They're all  round us now. Are we trapped?  
line 32659=>Who are they? ' 
line 32660=>     Gollum looked up. A  dark water was before him, and he was crawling  on 
line 32661=>the ground, this way and that, doubtful of the way. 'Yes, they are all round 
line 32662=>us,' he whispered. 'The tricksy lights. Candles  of corpses, yes, yes. Don't 
line 32663=>you heed them! Don't look! Don't follow them! Where's the master? ' 
line 32664=>     Sam looked back and found that Frodo had lagged again. He could not see 
line 32665=>
