line 32793=>     In fact with every step towards the gates of Mordor Frodo felt the Ring 
line 32794=>on  its chain about his neck grow  more burdensome.  He was now beginning to 
line 32795=>feel  it as an actual  weight  dragging him earthwards.  But far more he was 
line 32796=>troubled by the Eye: so he called it to  himself. It was that more  than the 
line 32797=>drag of the Ring that made him cower  and stoop as he walked. The Eye:  that 
line 32798=>horrible  growing sense of a  hostile will  that  strove with great power to 
line 32799=>pierce all shadows of  cloud, and earth, and  flesh, and to see you: to  pin 
line 32800=>you under its deadly gaze, naked, immovable. So thin, so frail and thin, the 
line 32801=>veils  were become  that still warded  it  off. Frodo  knew just  where  the 
line 32802=>present habitation and heart of that will now was: as certainly as a man can 
line 32803=>tell the  direction of the sun with his eyes shut. He was facing it, and its 
line 32804=>potency beat upon his brow.  
line 32805=>     Gollum probably felt something of the same sort.  But  what went  on in 
line 32806=>his wretched heart between the pressure of the Eye, and the lust of the Ring 
