line 32878=>between sleep and waking, until forgetfulness came over him. 
line 32879=>     Suddenly Sam woke up thinking that he heard his master calling.  It was 
line 32880=>evening. Frodo could not have called, for he had fallen asleep, and had slid 
line 32881=>down nearly to the  bottom of  the pit. Gollum was by  him. For a moment Sam 
line 32882=>thought that he was trying to  rouse Frodo; then he saw that it was  not so. 
line 32883=>Gollum was talking to himself. Smjagol was holding a  debate with some other 
line 32884=>thought  that used the same voice but  made it squeak and hiss. A pale light 
line 32885=>and a green light alternated in his eyes as he spoke. 
line 32886=>     `Smjagol promised,' said the first thought. 
line 32887=>     `Yes,  yes, my precious,' came  the  answer, 'we promised: to  save our 
line 32888=>Precious, not to let Him have it -- never. But it's going to Him yes, nearer  
line 32889=>every step.  What's the hobbit going  to  do  with it,  we wonders,  yes  we 
line 32890=>wonders.' 
line 32891=>     `I don't know. I can't help it. Master's  got it. Smjagol  promised  to 
line 32892=>help the master.' 
line 32893=>
line 32894=>####-     `Yes,  yes, to  help the master: the  master of the Precious. But if we 
line 32895=>was master, then we could help ourselfs, yes, and still keep promises.' 
line 32896=>     `But Smjagol said  he  would be very  very good.  Nice  hobbit! He took  
line 32897=>cruel rope off Smjagol's leg. He speaks nicely to me.' 
line 32898=>     'Very very good, eh, my precious? Let's be  good,  good as fish,  sweet  
line 32899=>one, but to ourselfs. Not hurt the nice hobbit, of course, no, no.' 
line 32900=>     `But the Precious holds the promise,' the voice of Smjagol objected. 
line 32901=>     `Then take it,' said  the other,  `and let's hold it ourselfs!  Then we 
line 32902=>shall be master, gollum! Make the other hobbit, the nasty suspicious hobbit, 
line 32903=>make him crawl, yes, gollum!' 
line 32904=>     `But not the nice hobbit? ' 
line 32905=>     `Oh no, not if it doesn't please us. Still he's a Baggins, my precious,  
line 32906=>yes,  a  Baggins.  A  Baggins  stole it. He  found it  and  he said nothing, 
line 32907=>nothing. We hates Bagginses.' 
line 32908=>     'No, not this Baggins.' 
line 32909=>     'Yes, every Baggins. All peoples  that  keep the Precious. We must have 
line 32910=>it!  ' 
line 32911=>     `But He'll see, He'll know. He'll take it from us! ' 
