line 32913=>orders, yes. Must take it. The Wraiths are searching. Must take it.' 
line 32914=>     'Not for Him! ' 
line 32915=>     'No, sweet  one. See, my precious: if  we  has it, then we  can escape, 
line 32916=>even from Him, eh? Perhaps we grows very strong, stronger than Wraiths. Lord 
line 32917=>Smjagol? Gollum  the Great?  The Gollum! Eat fish every day,  three times  a 
line 32918=>day; fresh from the sea. Most Precious Gollum! Must have it. We wants it, we 
line 32919=>wants it, we wants it!  ' 
line 32920=>     'But there's two of them. They'll wake too quick and kill  us,'  whined 
line 32921=>Smjagol in a last effort. `Not now. Not yet.' 
line 32922=>     'We  wants  it! But'  -- and here there  was a  long  pause, as if a new 
line 32923=>thought had wakened.  `Not yet,  eh? Perhaps not. She might help. She might, 
line 32924=>yes.' 
line 32925=>     `No, no! Not that way! ' wailed Smjagol. 
line 32926=>     `Yes! We wants it! We wants it! ' 
line 32927=>     Each time that  the second thought spoke, Gollum's  long hand crept out 
line 32928=>slowly, pawing towards Frodo, and then was drawn back with a jerk as 
line 32929=>Smjagol 
line 32930=>spoke  again. Finally  both  arms,  with long fingers  flexed and twitching, 
line 32931=>
line 32932=>####-clawed towards his neck. 
line 32933=>     Sam had lain  still, fascinated by this debate, but watching every move 
