line 33496=>     The  dusk was deep  when at length  they  set  out,  creeping over  the 
line 33497=>westward rim of the  dell, and fading like ghosts into the broken country on 
line 33498=>the borders of the road: The moon was now three nights from the full, but it  
line 33499=>did not climb over the mountains until nearly midnight, and the  early night 
line 33500=>was very dark. A single red light burned high up in the Tower s of the Teeth,  
line 33501=>but  otherwise no sign could be seen or heard of the sleepless watch  on the 
line 33502=>Morannon. 
line 33503=>     For  many  miles the red eye  seemed  to  stare at  them as they  fled, 
line 33504=>stumbling through a barren  stony country.  They did not dare  to  take  the 
line 33505=>road, but they  kept  it  on their left, following its line as  well as they 
line 33506=>could at a little distance.  At last, when  night  was growing old and  they 
line 33507=>were already weary, for they had taken only one short rest, the eye dwindled  
line 33508=>to a small fiery point a nd then vanished: they had turned the dark  northern 
line 33509=>shoulder of the lower mountains and were heading southwards. 
line 33510=>     With hearts  strangely  lightened they  now rested again, but  not  for  
line 33511=>long. They were  not going  quick enough for Gollum. By his reckoning it was 
line 33512=>nearly thirty leagues from the  Morannon to the cross-roads above Osgiliath, 
line 33513=>and he hoped to cover that distance in four journeys. So soon they struggled 
line 33514=>on once  more,  until the  dawn  began  to  spread  slowly in the wide  grey 
line 33515=>solitude. They had then  walked almost eight leagues; and the hobbits  could 
line 33516=>not have gone any further, even if they had dared. 
line 33517=>     The  growing  light revealed to them  a  land already, less  barren and 
line 33518=>ruinous. The mountains still loomed up ominously on their  left, but near at 
line 33519=>hand  they could  see the southward road,  now  bearing away  from the black 
line 33520=>
line 33521=>####-roots of the  hills and  slanting  westwards.  Beyond it were slopes covered 
line 33522=>with  sombre trees  like  dark clouds. but  all about  them  lay  a  tumbled 
line 33523=>heathland, grown with ling and broom  and cornel, and other shrubs that they 
line 33524=>did not know. Here and there they saw knots  of tall pine-trees.  The hearts 
line 33525=>of the hobbits rose again a little in spite of weariness: the  air was fresh 
line 33526=>and  fragrant, and it reminded them  of the uplands of the Northfarthing far 
line 33527=>away. It seemed good to be reprieved, to  walk in a land that had  only been 
line 33528=>for a few years  under the dominion of  the Dark Lord and was not yet fallen 
line 33529=>wholly into  decay. But they did not forget their danger, nor the Black Gate 
line 33530=>that was still all too near, hidden though it was behind the gloomy heights. 
line 33531=>They looked about for a hiding-place where they could shelter from evil eyes 
line 33532=>while the light lasted. 
line 33533=>     The  day passed uneasily. They lay deep  in the heather and counted out 
line 33534=>the  slow hours, in which  there seemed  little  change; for they were still 
line 33535=>under the shadows of the Ephel DÂ®ath, and the sun was veiled. Frodo slept at 
line 33536=>times, deeply and peacefully, either trusting Gollum or too tired to trouble 
line 33537=>about him; but Sam found it difficult to do more than doze, even when Gollum 
line 33538=>was plainly fast  asleep,  whiffling  and twitching in  his  secret  dreams.  
line 33539=>Hunger,  perhaps,  more than mistrust kept him wakeful: he had begun to long 
line 33540=>for a good homely meal, `something hot out of the pot'. 
line 33541=>     As soon as the land faded into a formless grey under coming night, they 
line 33542=>started  out  again. In  a little while  Gollum led  them  down  on  to  the 
line 33543=>southward road; and after that they went  on more quickly, though the danger 
line 33544=>was greater. Their ears were strained  for the sound of hoof or  foot on the 
line 33545=>road  ahead, or following them  from behind;  but the night passed, and they 
line 33546=>heard no sound of walker or rider. 
line 33547=>     The  road had been made in  a long lost  time:  and  for perhaps thirty 
line 33548=>miles below  the  Morannon it had been  newly repaired, but as it went south  
line 33549=>the wild encroached upon it. The handiwork of Men of old could still be seen 
line 33550=>in its straight sure  flight and level course:  now and again it cut its way 
line 33551=>through hillside slopes, or leaped over a stream upon a wide shapely arch of 
line 33552=>enduring masonry; but at  last  all signs  of stonework faded,  save  for  a  
line 33553=>broken pillar  here and  there,  peering out of bushes  at  the side, or old 
line 33554=>paving-stones still  lurking  amid weeds  and  moss.  Heather  and  trees and 
line 33555=>bracken  scrambled down  and  overhung  the banks, or sprawled out over  the 
line 33556=>surface. It dwindled at last to a country cart -road little  used; but it did 
line 33557=>not wind:  it held on its  own sure course and  guided them by  the swiftest  
line 33558=>
line 33559=>####-way. 
line 33560=>     So  they  passed into the  northern marches  of that land that Men once 
line 33561=>called Ithilien, a fair country of climbing woods and swift -falling streams.  
line 33562=>The  night  became  fine  under  star and round moon, and  it seemed  to the 
line 33563=>hobbits that the  fragrance  of the air grew as they went  forward; and from 
line 33564=>the  blowing and muttering of Gollum it  seemed that he noticed it  too, and 
line 33565=>did not relish it. At the first signs  of day  they halted  again.  They had 
line 33566=>come to the end of a long cutting, deep, and sheer -sided in  the middle,  by 
line 33567=>which the road clove its way through a stony  ridge. Now they climbed up the 
line 33568=>westward bank and looked abroad. 
line 33569=>     Day  was  opening in the sky, and they saw  that the mountains were now  
line 33570=>much further  off, receding ea stward in  a long curve  that was lost in  the 
line 33571=>distance. Before them, as they turned west, gentle slopes ran  down into dim 
line 33572=>hazes far  below. All about them were small woods of resinous trees, fir and 
line 33573=>cedar  and cypress. and other  kinds  unknown in the Shire, with wide glades 
line 33574=>among them; and  everywhere there was a wealth  of sweet -smelling  herbs and 
line 33575=>shrubs. The long journey from Rivendell had brought them far south of  their 
line 33576=>own  land,  but not until now in this more sheltered region had the  hobbits 
line 33577=>felt the change of clime.  Here Spring was  already busy about them:  fronds 
line 33578=>pierced  moss  and mould,  larches were  green-fingered, small flowers  were 
line 33579=>opening in the turf,  birds were singing. Ithilien, the garden of Gondor now 
line 33580=>desolate kept still a dishevelled dryad loveliness.  
line 33581=>     South  and  west  it looked  towards  the  warm lower vales  of Anduin, 
line 33582=>shielded  from   the  east  by  the  Ephel  DÂ®ath  and  yet  not  under  the 
line 33583=>mountain-shadow,  protected  from the north  by the  Emyn Muil, open  to the 
line 33584=>southern  airs and the moist winds from the Sea far  away.  Many great trees 
line 33585=>grew there,  planted  long ago,  falling  into untended age amid a  riot  of 
