line 33587=>pungent terebinth, of olive and of bay; and there were junipers and myrtles; 
line 33588=>and  thymes that grew in  bushes, or with their woody creeping stems mantled 
line 33589=>in deep tapestries the hidden stones; sages of many kinds putting forth blue 
