line 33608=>     Here they washed  themselves and  drank  their  fill at  the in-falling 
line 33609=>freshet. Then they sought for a resting-place, and a hiding-place: for  this 
line 33610=>land, fair-seeming  still, was nonetheless now territory of  the Enemy. They 
line 33611=>had not come  very far from the road, and yet even  in so short a space they 
line 33612=>had seen  scars of  the  old wars, and the newer wounds made by the Orcs and 
line 33613=>other foul servants of the Dark Lord:  a  pit of uncovered filth and refuse; 
line 33614=>trees hewn down wantonly  and  left to die, with evil runes or the fell sign 
