line 33869=>he said. `But there are no travellers in this land: only the servants of the 
line 33870=>Dark Tower, or of the White.' 
line 33871=>     `But  we are  neither,' said Frodo.  `And  travellers  we are, whatever  
line 33872=>Captain Faramir may say.' 
line 33873=>     'Then make  haste to declare yourselves and your errand,' said Faramir. 
line 33874=>'We  have  a  work  to  do,  and this is  no time or place  for riddling  or  
