line 34528=>     They stood on a wet floor of polished  stone, the doorstep, as it were, 
line 34529=>of a rough-hewn gate of rock opening dark behind them. But  in  front a thin 
line 34530=>veil  of water was hung, so  near that Frodo cou ld  have put an outstretched 
line 34531=>arm into it. It  faced westward. The level shafts  of the setting sun behind 
line 34532=>beat  upon it, and the red  light was broken  into many flickering  beams of 
line 34533=>ever -changing  colour. It  was as if  they  stood  at  the  window  of  some 
line 34534=>elven-tower, curtained with threaded  jewels  of silver and  gold, and ruby, 
line 34535=>sapphire and amethyst, all kindled with an unconsuming fire. 
line 34536=>     'At least by good chance we  came at the  right hour  to reward you for  
line 34537=>your patience,' said Faramir.  `This is the  Window  of the Sunset,  Henneth 
line 34538=>Annyn,  fairest  of all the falls of Ithilien, land  of  many fountains. Few 
line 34539=>strangers have ever seen it. But there is no kingly hall behind to match it. 
line 34540=>Enter now and see! ' 
line 34541=>     Even as he spoke the sun sank, and the fire faded in the flowing water.  
line 34542=>They  turned and passed under  the low forbidding  arch. At  once they found 
line 34543=>themselves in a rock -chamber, wide and rough, with an  uneven stooping roof.  
line 34544=>A  few torches were kindled  and cast a dim  light on the  glisten ing walls.  
line 34545=>Many men were already there. Others were  still coming in by twos and threes 
