line 34547=>gloom the hobbits saw that the cave was larger than they had guessed and was 
line 34548=>filled with gr eat store of arms and victuals.  
line 34549=>     'Well, here is  our refuge,'  said Faramir. `Not a place of  great ease 
line 34550=>but here you may pass  the night in peace. It is dry at least,  and there is 
line 34551=>food, though no fire. At one  time the water flowed  down  through this cave 
line 34552=>and out  of the  arch, but its  course was changed further  up the gorge, by 
line 34553=>workmen  of old, and the stream sent down in a fall  of  doubled height over  
line 34554=>the rocks  far above.  All the ways  into this grot were then sealed against  
