line 34556=>out:  that passage yonder by which you entered  blindfold,  and  through the  
line 34557=>Window-curtain into  a deep  bowl  filled  with knives of  stone. Now rest a  
line 34558=>
line 34559=>####-while, until the evening meal is set.' 
line 34560=>     The hobbits  were taken to a corner and given a  low bed to lie on,  if 
line 34561=>they wished. Meanwhile  men busied themselves about the cave, quietly and in 
line 34562=>orderly  quickness. Light  tables  were taken from the walls and  set  up on 
