line 34571=>accounted for, save  only the  great mymak:  what happened to him none could 
line 34572=>say. Of the enemy no movement could be seen; not even an orc-spy was 
line 34573=>abroad. 
line 34574=>     'You saw and heard nothing, Anborn?' Faramir asked of the latest comer. 
line 34575=>     `Well, no, lord,' said the man. `No Orc at least. But I saw, or thought 
