line 34954=>     Faramir turned to the man at his side. `Now what would you  say that it 
line 34955=>is,  Anborn? A squirrel, or a kingfisher? Are there black kingfishers in the 
line 34956=>night-pools of Mirkwood?  ' 
line 34957=>     `'Tis not a bird, whatever else it  be,' answered  Anborn. `It has four 
line 34958=>limbs and  dives manwise; a pretty mastery of the craft it  shows, too. What 
line 34959=>is it at? Seeking a way  up behind  the Curtain to our hidings?  It seems we 
line 34960=>
line 34961=>####-are discovered at last. I have my bow here, and I have posted other archers, 
line 34962=>nigh  as good  marksmen  as myself, on  either bank.  We  wait only for your 
