line 35182=>It is well  for you. What oath will  you swear never to return; and never to 
line 35183=>lead any living creature hither by word or sign?' 
line 35184=>     `Master knows,'  said Gollum with a  sidelong glance at Frodo. `Yes, he 
line 35185=>knows. We will promise Master, if he saves us. We'll promise to It, yes.' He 
line 35186=>crawled  to Frodo's feet.  'Save  us,  nice Master!  '  he whined.  `Smjagol 
line 35187=>promises to Precious, promises faithfully. Never come again, never speak, no 
line 35188=>
line 35189=>####-never! No, precious, no!' 
line 35190=>     `Are you satisfied? ' said Faramir. 
line 35191=>     `Yes,' said Frodo.  'At least, you must  either  accept this promise or 
line 35192=>carry out your law. You will get no more. But I promised that if he came  to  
line 35193=>me, he should not be harmed. And I would not be proved faithless.' 
line 35194=>     Faramir sat for a moment in thought. `Very good,' he  said at last.  `I  
line 35195=>surrender you to your master, to Frodo son of Drogo. Let him declare what he 
line 35196=>will do with you! ' 
line 35197=>     'But, Lord Faramir,' said Frodo bowing, `you have not yet declared your 
line 35198=>will  concerning  the said Frodo, and until  that is  made known, he  cannot 
line 35199=>shape his plans for himself  or his companions. Your judgement was postponed 
line 35200=>until the morning; but that is now at hand.' 
line 35201=>     `Then I  will declare my doom,' said Faramir. `As for you, Frodo, in so 
line 35202=>far as lies in me under higher  authority, I declare you  free in  the realm 
line 35203=>of, Gondor to the furthest of its ancient bounds; save only that neither you  
line 35204=>nor any that go with you have leave to come  to  this  place unbidden.  This 
line 35205=>doom  shall  stand for a  year and a day, and  then cease,  unless you shall 
line 35206=>before that term come to Minas Tirith and present yourself to  the  Lord and  
