line 35209=>protection shall be under my protection  and under the shield of Gondor. Are 
line 35210=>you answered? ' 
line 35211=>     Frodo bowed low. 'I am answered,' he  said, `and I place myself at your 
line 35212=>service, if that is of any worth to one so high and honourable.' 
line 35213=>     `It is  of  great  worth,' said  Faramir.  'And  now, do you  take this 
line 35214=>creature, this Smjagol, under your protection? ' 
line 35215=>     `I  do  take  Smjagol under  my  protection,' said  Frodo.  Sam  sighed 
