line 35318=>murder before now. I read it in him.' He sighed. 
line 35319=>     `Well, so we meet and  part,  Frodo son of Drogo. You have no  need  of 
line 35320=>soft words: I do  not hope to see you again on any other day under this Sun. 
line 35321=>But you shall go  now with my blessing upon you,  and upon  all your people. 
line 35322=>Rest a little while food is prepared for you. 
line 35323=>     'I would gladly learn how this creeping Smjagol became possessed of the 
line 35324=>Thing of which we speak, and how he lost it, but I will not trouble you now.  
line 35325=>If ever beyond  hope you return to the lands of the living and we retell our 
line 35326=>tales, sitting by a wall in the sun, laughing at  old  grief, you shall tell 
