line 35530=>passing through long dry aisles carpeted with a deep prickly mould. 
line 35531=>     On the further edge of this broad hill-back they stayed their march and  
line 35532=>crawled for hiding  underneath a  tangled  knot  of  thorns.  Their  twisted 
line 35533=>boughs, stooping to the ground, were overridden  by a clambering maze of old 
