line 35535=>bramble, and roofed with the first leaves and  shoots  of spring. There they 
line 35536=>lay for a  while, too tired yet to eat; and peering out through the holes in 
line 35537=>the covert they watched for the slow growth of day. 
line 35538=>     But no  day  came, only a dead brown twilight. In the East  there was a  
line 35539=>dull red glare under the lowering cloud: it  was not the red of dawn. Across 
line 35540=>the tumbled lands between, the mountains of the Ephel DÂ®ath frowned at 
line 35541=>them, 
line 35542=>black and shapeless below where night lay thick and did not pass away, above 
line 35543=>with  jagged  tops  and edges outlined  hard and  menacing against the fiery 
line 35544=>glow. Away to their right a great shoulder of the mountains  stood out, dark 
line 35545=>and black amid the shadows, thrusting westward. 
line 35546=>     `Which way do we go from here?' asked Frodo. `Is that the opening of-of 
line 35547=>the Morgul Valley, away over there beyond that black mass? ' 
line 35548=>     `Need we think about it yet?' said Sam, `Surely we're not going to move 
line 35549=>any more today, if day it is?' 
line 35550=>     `Perhaps not, perhaps not,' said Gollum.  `But we must go soon, to  the 
line 35551=>Cross-roads.  Yes,  to  the  Cross-roads. That's the  way  over  ther e  yes, 
line 35552=>Master.' 
line 35553=>     The red glare over Mordor  died  away. The twilight deepened  as  great 
line 35554=>vapours rose in the East and crawled above them. Frodo and Sam took a little 
line 35555=>food and then  lay down,  but Gollum was restless.  He would  not eat any of 
line 35556=>their food, but  he  drank  a little water and  then crawled about under the 
line 35557=>bushes, sniffing and muttering. Then. suddenly he disappeared. 
line 35558=>     `Off hunting, I suppose,' said Sam and yawned. It was his turn to sleep 
