line 35566=>with that he woke up. 
line 35567=>     `Silly!' he said  to himself, as he opened his eyes and wondered why he 
line 35568=>was lying  down under the hedge. `It's in  your pack all the time!'  Then he 
line 35569=>realized, first that the pipe might  be in his pack but he had  no leaf, and 
line 35570=>next that he was hundreds of miles from  Bag End. He sat up. It seemed to be 
