line 35574=>to be getting late!' 
line 35575=>     'No it isn't,' said Frodo.  `But  the day is getting darker instead  of 
line 35576=>lighter: darker and  darker. As far as I  can tell, it isn't midday yet, and 
line 35577=>you've only slept for about three hours.' 
line 35578=>     'I wonder what's up,' said  Sam. 'Is there  a storm coming? If  so it's 
line 35579=>going  to  be the  worst there ever was. We shall  wish  we were down a deep 
line 35580=>hole, not just stuck  under a hedge.' He listened. `What's that? Thunder, or  
line 35581=>drums, or what is it? ' 
line 35582=>     'I don't know,' said  Frodo. `It's been going on for a good while  now.  
line 35583=>Sometimes the ground seems  to  tremble, sometimes it seems to be  the heavy 
