line 35585=>     Sam looked  round.  `Where's Gollum?  ' he said. 'Hasn't he  come  back  
line 35586=>yet?' 
line 35587=>     `No,' said Frodo. `There's not been a sign or sound of him.' 
line 35588=>     `Well,  I  can't abide  him,'  said  Sam.  `In fact,  I've  never taken 
line 35589=>anything on a journey that I'd have been less sorry to lose  on the way. But 
line 35590=>it  would be just like him, after coming all these miles, to go and get lost  
line 35591=>now, just when we shall need him most  --  that is, if he's ever going  to be 
