line 35650=>before them: the Southward Road, winding its way about the outer feet of the 
line 35651=>mountains, until presently it plunged  into the great ring of trees.  
line 35652=>     'This is the only way,' whispered Gollum. 'No paths beyond the road. No 
line 35653=>paths. We must go to the Cross-roads. But make haste! Be silent! ' 
line 35654=>     As furtively as scouts within the campment of their enemies, they crept 
