line 35694=>
line 35695=>Chapter 8. The Stairs of Cirith Ungol 
line 35696=>
line 35697=> 
line 35698=> 
line 35699=>     Gollum  was  tugging  at  Frodo's  cloak  and  hissing  with  fear  and 
line 35700=>impatience. `We must go,' he said. `We mustn't stand here. Make haste!' 
line 35701=>     Reluctantly Frodo turned his back on the West and followed as his guide 
line 35702=>led  him, out into the darkness of the East. They left the ring of trees and 
line 35703=>crept along the road towards the mountains. This road, too, ran straight for  
line 35704=>a while,  but  soon it began to  bend  away southwards,  until it came right 
line 35705=>under the great shoulder of rock that they had seen from the distance. Black  
line 35706=>and  forbidding  it  loomed  above them, darker  than the  dark  sky behind. 
line 35707=>Crawl ing  under  its shadow the road  went on,  and rounding it sprang  east  
line 35708=>again and began to climb steeply. 
line 35709=>     Frodo and Sam were  plodding along with heavy hearts, no longer able to  
line 35710=>care greatly  about  their  peril. Frodo's head  was  bowed; his burden  was 
line 35711=>dragging him down again. As soon as the great  Cross-roads  had been passed, 
line 35712=>the weight of it, almost forgotten in Ithilien, had begun to grow once more. 
line 35713=>Now, feeling the way become steep before his feet, he looked wearily up; and 
line 35714=>then he  saw  it, even  as Gollum  had said  that he would: the city of  the 
line 35715=>Ringwraiths. He cowered against the stony bank. 
line 35716=>     A long-tilted  valley, a  deep gulf of shadow,  ran back far  into  the 
line 35717=>mountains. Upon the further side, some way  within the valley's arms high on 
line 35718=>a  rocky seat upon the black knees  of  the Ephel DÂ®ath, stood the walls and  
line 35719=>tower of Minas Morgul. All was dark about it, earth and sky, but it  was lit 
line 35720=>with light. Not the imprisoned moonlight welling through the marble walls of 
line 35721=>Minas  Ithil long ago, Tower of the  Moon, fair and radiant in the hollow of 
line 35722=>the hills. Paler  indeed than  the moon ailing in some  slow eclipse was the 
line 35723=>light of it now, wavering and blowing like a  noisome exhalation of decay, a  
line 35724=>corpse-light, a light that  illuminated  nothing.  In  the  walls  and tower  
line 35725=>windows showed, like countless black holes  looking inward  into  emptiness;  
line 35726=>but  the topmost course of the tower revolved slowly, first one way and then 
line 35727=>another, a huge ghostly head  leering into the night. For a moment the three 
line 35728=>companions  stood there, shrinking,  staring  up with unwilling eyes. Gollum 
line 35729=>was the first to recover. Again he pulled  at their cloaks urgently,  but he 
line 35730=>spoke no word. Almost he dragged them forward. Every step was reluctant, and 
line 35731=>time seemed to slow its pace. so that between the raising of a foot  and the 
line 35732=>
line 35733=>####-setting of it down minutes of loathing passed. 
line 35734=>     So they came  slowly  to the  white  bridge.  Here  the  road, gleaming 
