line 35833=>bridge below,  and Frodo's staring eyes followed him,  unable to  wink or to 
line 35834=>withdraw. Surely there was the Lord of the  Nine Riders returned to earth to 
line 35835=>lead his ghastly  host to battle? Here, yes here indeed was the haggard king 
line 35836=>whose cold  hand had smitten down the Ring-bearer with his deadly knife. The 
line 35837=>old wound throbbed with pain and a great chill spread towards Frodo's heart. 
line 35838=>     Even  as these thoughts  pierced him with dread  and held him  bound as 
line 35839=>with a  spell, the Rider halted suddenly, right  before the  entrance of the 
line 35840=>bridge, and behind him all the host stood still. There was  a pause, a  dead 
line 35841=>silence. Maybe it was  the Ring that called  to the  Wraith-lord, and for  a  
line 35842=>moment he was troubled, sensing some other power within his valley. This way 
