line 35848=>pressure was, he felt no  inclination now to yield to it. He  knew that  the 
line 35849=>Ring would only betray him, and that he had not, even if  he  put it on, the 
line 35850=>power  to face the  Morgul-king-not yet. There was no  longer any  answer to 
line 35851=>that command in his own will,  dismayed by terror though it was, and he  felt 
line 35852=>only the  beating upon him of a  great power from outside. It took his hand, 
