line 36184=>     `Hey you!' he said roughly. `What are you up to?' 
line 36185=>     'Nothing, nothing,' said Gollum softly. `Nice Master!' 
line 36186=>     `I daresay,' said Sam. 'But where have you been to  -- sneaking off and 
line 36187=>sneaking back, you old villain? ' 
line 36188=>
line 36189=>####-     Gollum withdrew himself, and a green glint  flickered under  his  heavy 
line 36190=>lids. Almost  spider -like  he  looked now, crouched  back on his bent limbs, 
line 36191=>with his  protruding eyes. The fleeting  moment  had  passed, beyond recall.  
line 36192=>`Sneaking,  sneaking!'  he  hissed.  'Hobbits always  so polite, yes. O nice 
line 36193=>hobbits! Smjagol brings them  up secret  ways that  nobody else  could find.  
line 36194=>Tired he is, thirsty  he is, yes thirsty; and he guides them and he searches 
line 36195=>for paths, and they say sneak, sneak. Very nice friends,  O yes my precious,  
line 36196=>very nice.' 
line 36197=>     Sam felt  a bit remorseful, though not more trustful. 'Sorry.' he said. 
line 36198=>'I'm sorry, but you startled me out of my sleep. And I  shouldn't  have been 
line 36199=>sleeping, and that made me a bit sharp.  But Mr.  Frodo.  he's that tired, I 
line 36200=>asked him to have a wink; and well,  that's how it is. Sorry. But where have 
line 36201=>you been to? ' 
line 36202=>     `Sneaking,' said Gollum, and the green glint did not leave his  eyes. 
line 36203=>     'O very well,' said Sam, `have it your own way! I don't suppose it's so 
line 36204=>far  from the truth. And now  we'd  better all  be  sneaking along together. 
line 36205=>What's the time? Is it today or tomorrow? ' 
line 36206=>     'It's tomorrow,' said Gollum, 'or this  was  tomorrow when hobbits went 
line 36207=>to sleep. Very foolish, very dangerous-if poor Smjagol wasn't sneaking about 
line 36208=>to watch.' 
line 36209=>     `I think we shall  get tired  of that word soon,' said Sam. 'But  never  
line 36210=>mind.  I'll  wake master up.' Gently he smoothed the hair back  fr om Frodo's 
line 36211=>brow, and bending down spoke softly to him. 
line 36212=>     `Wake up, Mr. Frodo! Wake up! ' 
line 36213=>     Frodo stirred  and  opened  his  eyes,  and  smiled, seeing Sam's  face 
line 36214=>bending over him.  `Calling me early  aren't you,  Sam?' he said. `It's dark 
line 36215=>still!  ' 
line 36216=>     'Yes  it's  always  dark here,' said  Sam. `But Gollum's come  back Mr. 
line 36217=>Frodo, and he says it's tomorrow. So we must be walking on. The last lap.' 
line 36218=>     Frodo drew a deep breath  and sat up. `The last lap! ' he said. 'Hullo, 
line 36219=>Smjagol! Found any food? Have you had any rest? ' 
line 36220=>     `No food, no rest, nothing for Smjagol,' said Gollum. `He's a sneak.' 
line 36221=>     Sam clicked his tongue, but restrained himself. 
line 36222=>     'Don't  take  names to  yourself,  Smjagol,'  said Frodo. 'It's  unwise 
line 36223=>whether they are true or false.' 
line 36224=>     `Smjagol has to take what's given  him,' answered Gollum. 'He was given 
line 36225=>that name by kind Master Samwise, the hobbit that knows so much.' 
line 36226=>
line 36227=>####-     Frodo looked at Sam. 'Yes sir,' he said. `I did use the word, waking up 
line 36228=>out of my sleep sudden and all  and finding him at hand. I said I was sorry, 
line 36229=>but I soon shan't be.' 
line 36230=>     'Come, let it pass then,' said Frodo. 'But now we seem to have  come to 
line 36231=>the point, you and  I, Smjagol. Tell me. Can we  find the rest of the way by 
line 36232=>ourselves?  We're in sight of  the pass, of a way in, and  if we can find it 
