line 36394=>fear of its revealing  light.  Aiya Edrendil Elenion Ancalima! he cried, and 
line 36395=>
line 36396=>####-knew  not what he had spoken; for it seemed that another voice spoke through 
line 36397=>his, clear, untroubled by the foul air of the pit. 
line 36398=>     But other  potencies  there are in  Middle-earth, powers of night,  and 
line 36399=>they are  old and strong. And She that  walked in the darkness had heard the 
line 36400=>Elves cry that cry far back in the deeps of time, and she had not heeded it, 
line 36401=>and it did  not daunt her now. Even as Frodo spoke he  felt  a great  malice 
line 36402=>bent upon him, and a deadly regard considering him. Not far down the tunnel, 
