line 36497=>sullen gloom. Yet it seemed to Frodo that he looked upon a morning of sudden 
line 36498=>hope. Almost he had reached  the  summit of the  wall. Only  a little higher  
line 36499=>now. The Cleft,  Cirith  Ungol, was before him, a dim  notch  in  the  black  
line 36500=>ridge, and the horns of rock darkling  in  the sky on either side.  A  short 
line 36501=>race, a sprinter's course and he would be through!  
line 36502=>     `The pass,  Sam! ' he  cried, not heeding the shrillness of  his voice, 
line 36503=>that  released  from  the choking airs of the  tunnel  rang out now high and 
line 36504=>wild. 'The  pass! Run, run, and we'll be  through-through before any one can 
line 36505=>stop us! ' 
line 36506=>     Sam came  up  behind as fast as he could  urge his legs; but glad as he 
line 36507=>was  to be free, he was uneasy, and as he ran, he kept on  glancing back  at 
line 36508=>the dark  arch of the tunnel, fearing to see eyes, or some  shape beyond his 
line 36509=>
line 36510=>####-imagining,  spring out in  pursuit. Too little did he or  his master know of 
line 36511=>the craft of Shelob. She had many exits from her  lair. 
line 36512=>     There agelong she had dwelt, an evil thing in spider -form, even such as 
line 36513=>once of old had lived in the Land of the Elves in the West that is now under  
line 36514=>the Sea, such as Beren fought in the Mountains of Terror  in Doriath, and so 
line 36515=>came to LÂ®thien upon the green sward amid the hemlocks in the moonlight 
line 36516=>long 
line 36517=>ago. How Shelob came there, flying from ruin, no tale tells, for out  of the 
line 36518=>Dark  Years  few tales  have come. But still she was  there, who  was  there 
line 36519=>before Sauron, and before the first  stone of Barad-dyr; and she served none 
line 36520=>but herself, drinking the blood of Elves and Men, bloated and grown fat with 
line 36521=>endless  brooding on her  feasts,  weaving  webs of shadow;  for all  living 
line 36522=>things  were  her  food,  and her  vomit  darkness.  Far and wide her lesser  
line 36523=>broods, bastards  of the miserable mates, her own offspring,  that she slew,  
line 36524=>spread from  glen to glen, from the Ephel DÂ®ath to the eastern hills, to Dol 
line 36525=>Guldur and the fastnesses of Mirkwood. But none could  rival her, Shelob the 
line 36526=>Great, last child of Ungoliant to trouble the unhappy world. 
line 36527=>     Already,  years before, Gollum had beheld her, Smjagol  who  pried into 
line 36528=>all dark  holes, and in past days he had  bowed  and worshipped her, and the 
line 36529=>darkness of  her evil will  walked through  all  the ways of  his  weariness 
line 36530=>beside him, cutting  him off from light and from regret. And he had promised 
line 36531=>to bring  her food. But her lust was  not his lust. Little  she  knew of  or  
line 36532=>cared for towers, or  rings, or  anything devised by mind  or hand, who only  
line 36533=>desired death for all others, mind and body, and for herself a glut of life. 
line 36534=>alone,  swollen  till  the  mountains  could no longer  hold her up and  the 
line 36535=>darkness could not contain her. 
line 36536=>     But that  desire  was yet far  away, and long  now had she been hungry, 
line 36537=>lurking  in  her den, while the power of  Sauron grew, and light and  living 
line 36538=>things forsook his borders; and the city in the valley was dead, and  no Elf 
line 36539=>or Man came near, only the unhappy Orcs. Poor  food  and  wary. But she must  
line 36540=>eat, and however busily  they delved new winding passages from  the pass and 
line 36541=>from their tower, ever she found  some way to snare them. But she lusted for  
line 36542=>sweeter meat. And Gollum had brought it to her. 
line 36543=>     `We'll see, we'll see,'  he  said often to himself, when the evil  mood 
line 36544=>was on him, as he walked the  dangerous road from  Emyn Muil to Morgul 
line 36545=>Vale, 
line 36546=>'we'll see. It may well be, O yes, it may well be  that when She throws away 
line 36547=>
line 36548=>####-the bones  and the empty garments, we  shall find it, we  shall  get it, the 
