line 36551=>know  it,  O  yes,  then we'll  pay  Her back,  my precious. Then  we'll pay 
line 36552=>everyone back! ' 
line 36553=>     So he thought in an inner chamber of  his cunning, which he still hoped 
line 36554=>to hide from  her,  even when he  had come  to her  again and had bowed  low 
line 36555=>before her while his companions slept. 
line 36556=>     And as for Sauron: he  knew where she lurked. It pleased  him that  she 
line 36557=>should dwell there hungry but unabated in  malice,  a more  sure  watch upon 
