line 36563=>he had no better uses for: he would have them driven to her hole, and  report  
line 36564=>brought back to him of the play she made. 
line 36565=>     So  they  both lived, delighting in  their  own devices,  and feared no 
line 36566=>assault, nor wrath,  nor any end of their wickedness. Never yet had any  fly 
line 36567=>escaped from Shelob's webs, and the greater now was her rage and hunger. 
line 36568=>     But  nothing of this evil which they had stirred  up against  them  did 
