line 37547=>drooping over the pool,  stood  a dead  tree, and  the falling drops dripped 
line 37548=>sadly from its barren and broken branches back into the clear water. 
line 37549=>
line 37550=>####-     Pippin glanced at  it  as he hurried after Gandalf. It looked mournful, 
line 37551=>he thought, and he wondered why the dead tree was  left in  this place where 
line 37552=>everything else was well tended. 
line 37553=>     Seven stars and seven stones and one white tree. 
line 37554=>     The words that Gandalf had murmured came back into  his mind. And  then 
line 37555=>he found himself at the doors of  the great hall beneath the gleaming tower; 
line 37556=>and behind the wizard he passed the tall silent door -wardens and entered the 
line 37557=>cool echoing shadows of the house of stone. 
line 37558=>     They walked  down  a paved passage, long and  empty, and  as  they went 
line 37559=>Gandalf spoke softly to Pippin. 'Be careful of your  words, Master Peregrin!  
line 37560=>This is  no time for  hobbit pertness. Thjoden is a kindly old man. Denethor  
line 37561=>is of another  sort, proud and subtle,  a  man  of far  greater  lineage and 
line 37562=>power, though  he is  not called a king. But he will  speak most to you, and 
line 37563=>question you much, since you  can tell him  of his son Boromir. He loved him 
line 37564=>greatly: too much  perhaps; and the more  so because they  were  unlike. But 
line 37565=>under cover  of  this love he will think it easier to  learn what he witches 
line 37566=>from you rather than  from me. Do not tell him more than you need, and leave 
line 37567=>quiet  the matter of Frodo's errand. I will deal with that in due  time. And 
line 37568=>say nothing about Aragorn either, unless you must.' 
line 37569=>     'Why  not? What is wrong with Strider?' Pippin  whispered. 'He meant to 
line 37570=>come here, didn't he? And he'll be arriving soon himself anyway.' 
line 37571=>     'Maybe,  maybe,' said Gandalf. 'Though if he comes, it is likely  to be 
line 37572=>in some way that no one expects, not even Denethor. It will be better so. At 
line 37573=>least he should come unheralded by us.' 
