line 37614=>     'It is,' said Gandalf. 'One  of the twain. The other is with Thjoden of 
line 37615=>Rohan and may come hereafter.  Halflings  they are,  as you see, yet this is 
line 37616=>not he of whom the omens spoke.' 
line 37617=>     'Yet  a  Halfling still,' said Denethor  grimly, 'and little love do  I 
line 37618=>bear the name, since those  accursed words  came to trouble our counsels and 
