line 37851=>     'Nine o'clock we'd call it in the Shire,' said Pippin aloud to himself.  
line 37852=>'Just  the time for a nice breakfast by the open window in spring  sunshine. 
line 37853=>
line 37854=>####-And  how I  should like  breakfast! Do these  people ever  have it, or is it 
line 37855=>over? And when do they have dinner, and where?' 
line 37856=>     Presently he noticed a man, clad  in  black and white, coming along the 
