line 37915=>     'Hobbit?' said Beregond. 
line 37916=>     'That is what we call ourselves,' said Pippin. 
line 37917=>     'I am glad to learn it,' said Beregond, 'for now I may say that strange 
line 37918=>accents  do not   mar fair speech,  and hobbits are  a  fair-spoken folk. But 
line 37919=>come! You shall make me acquainted with this good  horse. I love beasts, and 
line 37920=>we  see  them  seldom  in this  stony city;  for my  people  came  from  the 
line 37921=>mountain-vales, and before that from Ithilien. But fear not! The visit shall 
