line 37923=>     Pippin found that Shadowfax had been well housed and tended. For in the 
line 37924=>sixth circle, outside the walls of the citadel, there were some fair stables 
line 37925=>where  a   few  swift  horses  were  kept,  hard  by  the  lodgings  of  the 
line 37926=>errand-riders of  the  Lord: messengers always ready  to  go at  the  urgent 
