line 37938=>harness? It should be rich and fair.' 
line 37939=>     'None is  rich  and fair  enough for him,' said Pippin.  'He will  have 
line 37940=>none. If he will consent to bear you, bear you he does; and if not, well, no 
line 37941=>bit, bridle,  whip,  or  thong  will  tame  him.  Farewell, Shadowfax!  Have 
line 37942=>patience. Battle is coming.' 
line 37943=>     Shadowfax lifted up his head and neighed, so that the stable shook, and 
line 37944=>they covered their ears.  Then they took their leave, seeing that the manger  
line 37945=>was well filled. 
line 37946=>     'And now for our  manger,' said Beregond, and he led Pippin back to the 
