line 37998=>wains were  moving in  three  lines,  one swifter  drawn  by horses; another  
line 37999=>slower, great waggons with fair housings of many colours, drawn by oxen; and 
line 38000=>along the west rim of the road many smaller carts hauled by trudging men. 
line 38001=>     'That is the  road  to the  vales of  Tumladen and  Lossarnach, and the 
line 38002=>mountain-villages,  and then on  to Lebennin,' said  Beregond. 'There  go the 
line 38003=>last  of  the  wains that bear away to refuge the aged the children, and the 
