line 38015=>     'It was  a city,'  said Beregond, 'the chief city of Gondor,  of  which 
line 38016=>this  was only a fortress. For that is the ruin of Osgiliath  on either side 
line 38017=>of Anduin, which our enemies took and burned long ago. Yet we won it back in 
line 38018=>the  days of  the youth  of Denethor: not to dwell in,  but  to  hold as  an 
line 38019=>outpost, and  to rebuild  the  bridge for the  passage of our arms. And then 
