line 38033=>     'So  near to Mordor?' said  Beregond quietly.  'Yes,  there it lies. We 
line 38034=>seldom name it; but we have dwelt ever in sight of that shadow: sometimes it 
line 38035=>seems fainter and more distant;  sometimes nearer and darker. It  is growing 
line 38036=>and  darkening now; and  therefore  our fear  and disquiet grow too. And the 
line 38037=>Fell Riders, less  than a year ago they won back the crossings, and  many of 
line 38038=>our best men were  slain.  Boromir it  was that drove  the enemy at last back  
