line 38104=>     'Rightly said!' cried Beregond, rising and striding to and  fro.  'Nay, 
line 38105=>though all things  must come  utterly to an  end  in  time, Gondor shall not 
line 38106=>perish yet. Not though  the walls be taken by a reckless foe that will build 
line 38107=>a hill of carrion before them. There  are still other fastnesses, and secret 
line 38108=>ways of escape  into the mountains. Hope and memory shall live still in some 
line 38109=>hidden valley where the grass is green.' 
line 38110=>     'All the same, I  wish it was over for good or ill.' said Pippin. 'I am 
line 38111=>no warrior at all and dislike any thought of battle; but waiting on the edge 
