line 38113=>already! I should  be happier, if we  were not obliged  to stand and  watch, 
line 38114=>making  no move, striking nowhere first. No stroke would have been struck in 
line 38115=>Rohan, I think, but for Gandalf.' 
line 38116=>     'Ah, there  you  lay  your finger on  the  sore  that  many feel!' said 
line 38117=>Beregond. 'But things may change when Faramir returns. He is bold, more bold 
line 38118=>than many deem; for in these days men are slow to believe that a captain can 
line 38119=>
line 38120=>####-be wise and learned in the scrolls of lore and song, as he is, and yet a man 
line 38121=>of hardihood  and swift  judgement in the field. But such is  Faramir.  Less 
