line 38263=>towards them like a gathering wind. Then there was a loud trumpet-blast, and 
line 38264=>all about them people were shouting. 
line 38265=>     'Forlong! Forlong!' Pippin  heard men calling.  'What do  they say?' he 
line 38266=>asked. 
line 38267=>     'Forlong  has come,' Bergil answered; 'old Forlong the Fat, the Lord of 
line 38268=>Lossarnach. That is where  my grandsire  lives. Hurrah! Here he is. Good old 
line 38269=>Forlong!' 
line 38270=>
line 38271=>####-     Leading the line there came walking a big thick -limbed horse, and on it 
