line 38320=>     'Farewell  for  this  time,'  said  Bergil.  'Take  my  greetings to my 
line 38321=>:father, and thank him for the company that he sent. Come again soon, I beg.  
line 38322=>Almost  I wish now that there was no war,  for we might have  had some merry 
line 38323=>times. We might have journeyed to Lossarnach, to my grandsire's house; it is 
line 38324=>good to be  there in Spring, the  woods and fields are  full of flowers. But 
line 38325=>maybe we will go thither together  yet.  They will never overcome our  Lord, 
line 38326=>and my father is very valiant. Farewell and return!' 
