line 38498=>     'They are a strange company, these  newcomers,'  said Gimli. 'Stout men 
line 38499=>and lordly  they are,  and the  Riders  of Rohan look  almost as boys beside 
line 38500=>them; for they are grim men  of face, worn like weathered rocks for the most  
line 38501=>part, even as Aragorn himself; and they are silent.' 
line 38502=>     'But even as Aragorn they  are courteous, if they break  their silence.' 
line 38503=>said  Legolas. 'And have  you marked  the brethren Elladan and Elrohir? Less 
line 38504=>sombre is their  gear than  the  others', and  they are fair and  gallant as 
line 38505=>Elven-lords;  and that  is not  to be wondered  at in the sons of  Elrond of 
line 38506=>Rivendell.' 
line 38507=>     'Why have  they come? Have you heard?' asked Merry. He had now dressed, 
line 38508=>and he flung  his grey cloak about his shoulders; and  the  three passed out 
