line 38510=>     'They answered  a  summons,  as you  heard,'  said Gimli. 'Word  came to 
line 38511=>Rivendell, they  say: Aragorn has need of his kindred. Let the DÂ®nedain ride 
line 38512=>to him in Rohan! But whence this message came they are now in doubt. 
line 38513=>Gandalf 
line 38514=>sent it, I would guess.' 
line 38515=>
line 38516=>####-     'Nay, Galadriel,' said  Legolas. 'Did she not speak  through Gandalf of 
line 38517=>the ride of the Grey Company from the North?' 
line 38518=>     'Yes,  you have it,' said Gimli. 'The Lady of  the Wood! She  read many 
line 38519=>hearts and  desires. Now why did  not we wish for some  of our own kinsfolk, 
line 38520=>Legolas?' 
line 38521=>     Legolas stood before the gate and turned his bright eyes away north and 
line 38522=>east, and his fair face was troubled. 'I do not  think that any would come,' 
line 38523=>he answered. 'They have no need to ride to war; war already marches on their 
line 38524=>own lands.' 
line 38525=>     For  a while the three companions walked together, speaking of this and 
line 38526=>that turn of the battle, and they went down from the broken gate, and passed 
