line 39020=>back they rode  the mountain-fields, until they came to  a  bridge over  the 
line 39021=>growing torrent and found a road that went down into the land. 
line 39022=>     Lights went out in house  and hamlet as they came, and doors  were shut, 
line 39023=>and folk that were  afield cried in terror and ran  wild  like  hunted deer. 
line 39024=>Ever there rose the same cry in the gathering  night: 'The King of the Dead!  
line 39025=>The King of the Dead is come upon us!' 
line 39026=>     Bells  wer e ringing far  below, and all men  fled  before  the face  of 
