line 39037=>None of the people of the valley dared to approach it, nor would  they dwell  
line 39038=>near;  for  they said  that it was a trysting-place  of  the Shadow-men, and 
line 39039=>there  they would  gather in  times  of fear, thronging round  the Stone and 
line 39040=>whispering. 
line 39041=>     To tha t Stone  the Company came and halted in the  dead  of night. Then  
line 39042=>Elrohir gave to Aragorn a silver horn, and he blew upon it and  it seemed to 
line 39043=>those that stood near  that they heard a sound of answering  horns, as if it 
