line 39062=>hedged them round. 
line 39063=>     But when the dawn came, cold and pale, Aragorn rose at once, and he led  
line 39064=>the Company forth upon the journey of greatest haste and  weariness that any 
line 39065=>among them  had known, save he  alone, and only his will held them to go on. 
line 39066=>No  other mortal Men  could  have endured it, none but the  DÂ®nedain  of the 
