line 40269=>     The retreat became a rout. Already men were breaking away, flying  wild  
line 40270=>and witless here and there, flinging away their weapons, crying out in fear, 
line 40271=>falling to the ground. 
line 40272=>     And then a trumpet rang from the Citadel, and Denethor at last released 
line 40273=>the sortie. Drawn up  within  the shadow of the  Gate and under the  looming 
line 40274=>walls outside they had waited for his signal: all the  mounted men that were 
line 40275=>left in the City.  Now they  sprang forward, formed, quickened to  a gallop, 
