line 40365=>steel or  fire, unbreakable except  by some  convulsion that would rend  the 
line 40366=>very earth on which it stood. 
line 40367=>     'Nay,'  they said,  'not if  the Nameless One himself should come,  not 
line 40368=>even he could enter here while  we yet live.'  But some answered: 'While  we 
line 40369=>yet live? How long? He has  a weapon that has brought low many strong places 
line 40370=>since the world began. Hunger. The roads are cut. Rohan will not come.' 
line 40371=>     But the engines did not waste shot upon the indomitable wall. It was no 
line 40372=>brigand or orc-chieftain that ordered the assault upon the Lord  of Mordor's 
line 40373=>greatest  foe. A  power and mind of malice guided  it. As soon as  the great 
line 40374=>catapults were set, with many yells and the creaking of rope and winch, they 
line 40375=>began to throw  missiles marvellou sly high, so that they passed  right above 
