line 40396=>few left in Minas Tirith who had the heart to stand up and defy the hosts of 
line 40397=>Mordor.  For yet another weapon, swifter than hunger,  the Lord of the  Dark 
line 40398=>Tower had: dread and despair. 
line 40399=>     The Nazgyl came again, and  as  their  Dark Lord now grew and put forth  
line 40400=>his strength, so their voices, which uttered only his  will and  his malice, 
line 40401=>were filled with  evil and  horror. Ever they circled  above the  City, like 
