line 40404=>More unbearable they became, not  less, at each new cry.  At length even the 
line 40405=>stout-hearted would  fling  themselves to the  ground as the  hidden  menace 
line 40406=>passed  over  them,  or they would  stand, letting  their  weapons fall from 
line 40407=>nerveless hands while into their minds a blackness came, and they thought no 
line 40408=>more of war, but only of hiding and of crawling, and of death. 
line 40409=>     During all this black day Faramir  lay  upon his bed  in the chamber of 
line 40410=>the White Tower, wandering  in  a  desperate fever; dying someone  said, and 
