line 40418=>grew old before his eyes, as if something had snapped in his proud will, and 
line 40419=>his stern mind was  overthrown. Grief maybe had wrought it, and  remorse. He 
line 40420=>saw tears on that once tearless face, more unbearable than wrath. 
line 40421=>     'Do not weep, lord,' he stammered. 'Perhaps he will get well. Have  you  
line 40422=>asked Gandalf?' 
line 40423=>     'Comfort me  not  with wizards!' said Denethor.  'The  fool's  hope has 
line 40424=>failed.  The Enemy has  found it, and now his power waxes; he sees  our very 
line 40425=>thoughts, and all we do is ruinous. 
line 40426=>     'I sent my  son forth,  unthanked, unblessed, out  into needless peril, 
line 40427=>and here he lies with poison in his veins. Nay, nay, whatever may now betide 
line 40428=>in war, my line too is  ending, even the House  of the Stewards  has failed. 
line 40429=>
line 40430=>####-Mean  folk shall rule  the last remnant of the Kings of Men, lurking in  the 
