line 40434=>the end. But that is near. Follow whom you will,  even the Grey Fool, though 
line 40435=>his hope has failed. Here I stay.' 
line 40436=>     So it was that Gandalf took command of the last defence of the City  of 
line 40437=>Gondor.  Wherever he came  men's  hearts would  lift  again,  and the winged 
line 40438=>shadows pass from memory. Tirelessly he strode  from Citadel to  Gate,  from 
