line 40511=>at length to  a door in the rearward wall of the sixth circle. Fen Hollen it 
line 40512=>was called, for it was kept ever shut save at times of funeral, and only the 
line 40513=>Lord of  the  City might use that  way, or those who  bore the token of  the 
line 40514=>tombs and tended the houses of the  dead. Beyond it went a winding road that 
line 40515=>descended in  many curves down  to the  narrow  land  under  the  shadow  of 
line 40516=>Mindolluin's  precipice  where stood the mansions of the dead Kings  and  of 
line 40517=>their Stewards.  
line 40518=>     A porter  sat in a  little house beside  the way,  and with fear in his 
line 40519=>eyes he came  forth bearing  a lantern in his hand. At the Lord's command he 
line 40520=>unlocked the door, and  silently it  swung  back; and  they passed  through, 
line 40521=>taking  the lantern from his  hand. It was dark on the climbing road between 
line 40522=>ancient  walls  and   many -pillared   balusters   looming  in  the   swaying 
