line 41422=>Much loss and sorrow has befallen us.' 
line 41423=>     'Then let us avenge it, ere  we speak  of it!'  said Aragorn,  and they 
line 41424=>rode back to battle together. 
line 41425=>     Hard  fighting and long  labour they had  still; for the Southrons were 
line 41426=>bold  men and grim, and fierce in despair; and  the Easterlings  were strong 
line 41427=>and war-hardened and asked for no quarter. And so in this place and that, by 
