line 42335=>the care of his friends.' 
line 42336=>     'They are a remarkable race,' said the Warden, nodding his head.  'Very 
line 42337=>tough in the fibre, I deem.' 
line 42338=>     At the  doors of the Houses many were already gathered to  see Aragorn,  
line 42339=>and they  followed  after him; and when at last he  had supped, men came and 
line 42340=>prayed that he would heal their kinsmen or their friends whose lives were in 
line 42341=>peril through hurt or wound, or who lay under the Black  Shadow. And 
line 42342=>Aragorn 
line 42343=>arose and went out, and he sent for  the sons of  Elrond,  and together they 
line 42344=>laboured  far into the  night. And word went through the City: 'The  King is 
line 42345=>come again indeed.' And they named  him Elfstone, because of the green stone 
line 42346=>that  he wore, and so  the name  which it was for etold at his  birth that he 
line 42347=>should bear was chosen for him by his own people. 
line 42348=>     And when he  could labour no  more,  he cast his  cloak  about him, and 
line 42349=>slipped out of the City, and went to his tent just ere dawn and  slept for a  
line 42350=>little. And in the morning the banner of  Dol Amroth, a  white ship  like  a  
line 42351=>swan upon blue water, floated from the Tower, and men looked up and 
line 42352=>wondered 
line 42353=>if the coming of the King had been but a dream. 
