line 42481=>great speed. Silent they were, but there was a gleam in  their eyes. In  the 
line 42482=>uplands of Lamedon they overtook our horses, and  swept round us, and  would 
line 42483=>have passed us by, if Aragorn had not forbidden them. 
line 42484=>     'At his command they fell back. "Even the shades of Men are obedient to 
line 42485=>his will," I thought. "They may serve his needs yet! " 
line 42486=>     'One day of light  we  rode, and then  came the  day  without dawn, a nd 
