line 42522=>of  the ships had put off, seeking to escape down the River  or to reach  the 
line 42523=>far shore; and many of  the  smaller  craft were  ablaze.  But the Haradrim, 
line 42524=>being  now  driven  to the brink, turned at  bay,  and they were  fierce  in 
line 42525=>despair; and they laughed when they looked on us, for they were a great army 
