line 42709=>perish utterly in  a black battle far from the living lands; so that even if 
line 42710=>Barad-dyr  be thrown down, we shall not live to  see a new age.  But this, I 
line 42711=>deem, is our  duty. And better so than  to perish nonetheless - as we surely 
line 42712=>shall, if we sit here  - and know as we die that no new age shall be.' 
line 42713=>     They were  silent for a while.  At  length Aragorn  spoke.  'As  I have 
line 42714=>begun, so I  will go on.  We  come  now  to the  very brink, where hope  and 
