line 43070=>world  stood  still,  but their  hearts were dead and their last  hope gone. 
line 43071=>Pippin who stood behind Prince Imrahil sprang forward with a cry of grief.  
line 43072=>     'Silence!' said Gandalf sternly, thrusting him back;  but the Messenger  
line 43073=>laughed aloud. 
line 43074=>     'So you  have yet another of these imps  with you!' he cried. 'What use 
line 43075=>you  find in them I cannot guess; but to send them as  spies into Mordor  is 
line 43076=>beyond even your  accustomed folly. Still, I thank him, for it is plain that 
line 43077=>this brat  at  least has seen these tokens  before, and it would be vain for 
