line 43079=>     'I do not wish to  deny  them,' said Gandalf. 'Indeed, I know them  all 
line 43080=>and all  their history,  and despite your scorn,  foul Mouth of  Sauron, you  
line 43081=>cannot say as much. But why do you bring them here?' 
line 43082=>     'Dwarf-coat,  elf-cloak, blade of the downfallen West, and spy from the 
line 43083=>little rat-land  of the Shire-nay; do not  start! We know it well - here are 
line 43084=>the marks  of a  conspiracy. Now,  maybe  he that bore  these  things was  a  
line 43085=>creature that you would not grieve to lose, and maybe otherwise: one dear to  
line 43086=>you, perhaps? If so, take swift counsel with what little wit is left to you. 
line 43087=>For  Sauron does not love  spies, and what his fate  shall be depends now on 
