line 43089=>     No one answered him;  but he  saw their faces  grey with  fear and  the 
line 43090=>horror  in their eyes, and he laughed again, for it  seemed to him  that his 
line 43091=>sport went well. 'Good, good!' he  said. 'He was dear to you, I see. Or else 
line 43092=>his  errand was one that you did not wish to fail? It  has. And now he shall 
line 43093=>endure the slow torment of years, as long and  slow as our arts in the Great 
line 43094=>Tower can contrive, and never  be released,  unless maybe when he is changed 
line 43095=>and  broken,  so  that  he may come  to you, and you  shall see what you have  
line 43096=>done. This shall surely be-unless you accept my Lord's terms.' 
line 43097=>     'Name  the  terms,'  said Gandalf steadily,  but  those nearby  saw the 
line 43098=>anguish in  his  face,  and now he  seemed an  old and wizened man, crushed, 
line 43099=>defeated at la st. They did not doubt that he would accept. 
line 43100=>     'These are the terms,' said the  Messenger, and smiled as he eyed  them 
line 43101=>one by one. 'The rabble of  Gondor and  its deluded allies shall withdraw at 
line 43102=>once beyond the Anduin, first taking oaths never  again to assail Sauron the 
line 43103=>
line 43104=>####-Great  in arms, open or  secret. All lands east of Anduin  shall be Sauron's 
line 43105=>for  ever, solely. West of the Anduin as  far as the Misty Mountains and the 
