line 43108=>help  to rebuild Isengard which they have wantonly destroyed, and that shall 
line 43109=>be Sauron's, and there his lieutenant shall dwell: not Saruman, but one more 
line 43110=>worthy of trust.' 
line 43111=>     Looking in  the Messenger's  eyes they read his thought.  He was to  be  
line 43112=>that lieutenant, and gather all that remained of the West under his sway; he 
line 43113=>would be their tyrant and they his slaves.  
line 43114=>     But Gandalf said:  'This is much  to demand for  the  delivery  of  one 
line 43115=>servant: that your Master should receive in exchange what he must else fight  
line 43116=>many a war to gain! Or has the field of Gondor destroyed his hope in war, so 
