line 43121=>     It  seemed then to Gandalf,  intent, watching  him as a  man engaged in 
line 43122=>fencing with a deadly foe, that for the taking of a breath the Messenger was 
line 43123=>at a loss; yet swiftly he laughed again. 
line 43124=>     'Do  not bandy words in  your  insolence with  the Mouth of Sauron!' he 
line 43125=>cried. 'Surety you crave! Sauron gives none. If you sue for his clemency you  
