line 43129=>upraised hand   the  foul Messenger recoiled, and  Gandalf  coming seized and 
line 43130=>took from him  the tokens: coat,  cloak, and sword. 'These we  will take  in 
line 43131=>memory of our friend,' he cried.  'But  as for your  terms, we  reject  them 
line 43132=>utterly. Get you gone, for your embassy is over and death is near to you. We 
line 43133=>did not  come here  to waste words in treating  with Sauron,  faithless  and 
line 43134=>accursed; still less with one of his slaves. Begone!' 
line 43135=>     Then the Messenger of Mordor laughed no more. His face was twisted with 
line 43136=>amazement and anger to the  likeness of some wild beast that, as it crouches 
line 43137=>on  its  prey, is smitten on the muzzle with a stinging rod. Rage filled him 
line 43138=>and his mouth  slavered, and shapeless  sounds of fury came  strangling from 
line 43139=>his throat. But he looked at the fell faces of the Captains and their deadly 
