line 43141=>
line 43142=>####-upon his  steed, and with his company galloped madly back to  Cirith Gorgor. 
line 43143=>But  as they went his soldiers blew their horns in signal long arranged; and 
line 43144=>even before they came to the gate Sauron sprang his trap. 
line 43145=>     Drums rolled and fires leaped up.  The  great doors  of the  Black Gate 
line 43146=>swung  back wide. Out  of  it streamed a great host  as  swiftly as swirling 
line 43147=>waters when a sluice is lifted. 
line 43148=>     The Captains mounted  again  and rode back, and from the host of Mordor 
line 43149=>there went up a jeering yell. Dust  rose smothering the air,  as from nearby 
line 43150=>there marched up an army of Easterlings  that  had  waited for the signal in 
line 43151=>the shadows of Ered Lithui beyond the further Tower.  Down from the hills on 
