line 43230=>Chapter 1. The Tower of Cirith Ungol 
line 43231=>
line 43232=> 
line 43233=> 
line 43234=>     Sam roused himself painfully from the ground. For a  moment he wondered 
line 43235=>where he was, and then all the misery and despair returned to him. He was in 
line 43236=>the deep dark outside the  under -gate of the orcs'  stronghold;  its  brazen 
line 43237=>doors were shut. He must have fallen  stunned when he hurled himself against  
line 43238=>them; but  how  long he had lain there he did not know. Then he  had been on 
line 43239=>fire, desperate and furious;  now he was shivering and cold. He crept to the 
line 43240=>doors and pressed his ears against them. 
line 43241=>     Far  within  he  could hear  faintly the voices of ores clamouring, but 
line 43242=>soon they stopped or  passed out of hearing,  and  all was still.  His  head 
line 43243=>ached and his eyes saw phantom lights in  the  darkness, but he struggled to 
line 43244=>steady  himself and  think. It  was clear at any rate that he had no hope of 
line 43245=>getting into the orc-hold by that gate; he might wait  there for days before 
line 43246=>it was opened, and he could  not wait: time  was  desperately precious. He no 
line 43247=>longer had any doubt about his duty: he must rescue  his master or perish in 
line 43248=>the attempt. 
line 43249=>     'The  perishing is more  likely, and will be a lot  easier  anyway,' he 
line 43250=>said grimly to  himself,  as  he sheathed Sting and turned  from  the brazen 
