line 44232=>     The water was cool but not icy, and it had an unpleasant taste, a t once 
line 44233=>bitter and  oily, or  so they would have said at home. Here it seemed beyond 
line 44234=>all  praise, and beyond fear  or  prudence. They  drank their  fill, and Sam 
line 44235=>replenished his water -bottle. After that Frodo felt easier, and they went on 
line 44236=>for several miles, until the broadening of the road and  the beginnings of a  
line 44237=>rough wall along its edge warned them that they were drawing near to another  
line 44238=>orc-hold. 
line 44239=>     'This  is  where  we  turn aside, Sam,' said  Frodo. 'And we  must turn 
line 44240=>east.'  He  sighed as he looked a t  the gloomy ridges across the  valley. 'I  
line 44241=>have just about  enough strength left to find  some hole  away up there. And  
line 44242=>then I must rest a little.' 
line 44243=>     The river -bed  was now some way  below the path. They scrambled down to 
line 44244=>it,  and began to cross  it. To their surprise they came upon dark pools fed 
line 44245=>by  threads  of water trickling down from some source  higher up the valley.  
line 44246=>
line 44247=>####-Upon its  outer marges under the westward mountains Mordor was a dying 
line 44248=>land, 
line 44249=>but it was not yet dead. And here things still grew, harsh, twisted, bitter, 
line 44250=>struggling  for life. In  the glens of the Morgai on the other  side  of the 
line 44251=>valley low scrubby trees lurked and clung, coarse grey grass-tussocks fought  
line 44252=>with the stones,  and withered mosses crawled on them; and  everywhere great 
line 44253=>writhing, tangled brambles sprawled. Some  had  long stabbing  thorns,  some 
line 44254=>hooked barbs that rent like knives. The sullen shrivelled leaves of  a  past  
line 44255=>year  hung on  them,  grating  and  rattling  in  the  sad airs,  but  their 
line 44256=>maggot-ridden buds were  only  just  opening. Flies,  dun or grey, or black, 
line 44257=>marked like ores with a red  eye-shaped blotch, buzzed and stung;  and above 
