line 44273=>the air of Mordor  that dried the mouth. When Sam thought of water  even his 
line 44274=>hopeful spirit quailed.  Beyond  the Morgai there was the dreadful plain  of 
line 44275=>Gorgoroth to cross.  
line 44276=>     'Now  you go to  sleep first, Mr. Frodo,' he said.  'It's getting  dark 
line 44277=>again. I reckon this day is nearly over.' 
line 44278=>     Frodo sighed and was  asleep almost before  the words were  spoken. Sam 
