line 46245=>others that dwelt afar went back to their homes  rejoicing; but in the  City 
line 46246=>there was  labour of many willing hands to  rebuild  and renew and to remove 
line 46247=>all the scars of war and the memory of the darkness.  
line 46248=>     The hobbits still remained in Minas Tirith, with Legolas and Gimli; for  
line 46249=>Aragorn  was  loth for the fellowship  to be dissolved. 'At  last  all  such 
line 46250=>things must end,' he said, 'but I would have you wait a little while longer: 
line 46251=>for  the end  of the deeds  that you have  shared in has not yet come. A day 
line 46252=>draws near that  I have looked for in all the years of my manhood,  and when 
line 46253=>it comes I would have my friends beside me.' But of that day he would say no 
line 46254=>more. 
line 46255=>     In those days the Companions of the Ring dwelt together in a fair house 
