line 46257=>Gandalf:  'Do you know what this  day is that  Aragorn speaks of? For we are 
line 46258=>happy here, and I don't wish to go; but the days are running away, and Bilbo  
line 46259=>is waiting; and the Shire is my home.' 
line 46260=>     'As for  Bilbo,' said Gandalf, 'he is waiting for the same day, and  he 
line 46261=>knows what keeps you. And as for the passing of the days, it is now only May 
line 46262=>and high summer is not yet in; and though all things may seem changed, as if 
line 46263=>an  age of the world had gone by,  yet to the trees and the grass it is less 
line 46264=>than a year since you set out.' 
line 46265=>     'Pippin,' said Frodo, 'didn't you say  that Gandalf was less close than 
line 46266=>of old? He was weary of his labours then, I think. Now he is recovering.' 
line 46267=>     And Gandalf said: 'Many  folk  like to know beforehand what is to be set 
line 46268=>on the table; but those who have laboured  to prepare the feast like to keep 
line 46269=>their secret;  for  wonder makes the words of  praise  louder.  And  Aragorn 
line 46270=>himself waits for a sign.' 
line 46271=>     There came a day when  Gandalf could not  be  found, and  the Companions 
