line 46328=>ripeness, yet the life within may then lie sleeping through many long years, 
line 46329=>and none can foretell the time in which it will awake. Remember this. For if 
line 46330=>ever  a fruit ripens,  it should  be planted, lest  the  line die out of the 
line 46331=>world. Here it has lain. hidden on the mountain, even as the race of Elendil 
line 46332=>lay hidden in the wastes of the North. Yet the line of Nimloth is older  far 
line 46333=>than your line, King Elessar.' 
line 46334=>     Then Aragorn laid his hand  gently to the sapling, and lo! it seemed to 
