line 47099=>disquieted,  for it seemed  plain  to them  that old Barliman was putting  a  
line 47100=>brave  face on some trouble.  Things were not what they  had been.  But they 
line 47101=>said nothing, and waited. 
line 47102=>     As  they expected Mr. Butterbur came to the parlour after supper to see 
