line 47107=>this evening, anyway. But if you could spare me half an  hour before you  go 
line 47108=>to  your beds, I would dearly like to have some talk with you, quiet-like by 
line 47109=>ourselves.' 
line 47110=>     'That  is  just what we should like,  too,'  said Gandalf. 'We  are not 
line 47111=>tired.  We have been taking things easy.  We were wet, cold and hungry,  but 
line 47112=>all  that you  have  cured.  Come, sit down!  And if you have any pipe-weed, 
line 47113=>we'll bless you.' 
line 47114=>
line 47115=>####-     'Well, if you'd called  for anything else, I'd have been happier,' said 
line 47116=>Butterbur. 'That's just a thing that we're  short of, seeing how  we've only 
line 47117=>got  what we  grow ourselves,  and  that's not enough. There's none to be had 
line 47118=>from the Shire these days. But I'll do what I can.' 
line 47119=>     When he came back he brought them enough to last them for a day or two, 
