line 47211=>then you'll have some fair folk riding through.' 
line 47212=>     'Well,  that sounds more hopeful, I'll  allow,' said Butterbur. 'And it 
line 47213=>will be good for  business, no doubt. So long as he lets Bree alone.' 
line 47214=>     'He will,' said Gandalf. 'He knows it and loves it.' 
line 47215=>     'Does he now?' said Butterbur looking puzzled. 'Though I'm sure I don't 
