line 47219=>good, Gandalf. It's been uncommon good, since you came in the autumn of last  
line 47220=>year and put a good word on it. And that's been a comfort in trouble, I will 
line 47221=>say.' 
line 47222=>     'Ah!' said Sam. 'But he says your beer is always good.' 
line 47223=>     'He says?' 
line 47224=>     'Of course he does. He's Strider. The chief of the Rangers. Haven't you  
line 47225=>got that into your head yet?' 
line 47226=>     It went in at last, and  Butterbur's face was  a study in  wonder.  The 
line 47227=>eyes in his broad face grew round, and his mouth opened wide, and he gasped. 
line 47228=>
line 47229=>####-'Strider!' he exclaimed when he  got back his breath.  'Him with a crown and 
line 47230=>all and a golden cup! Well, what are we coming to?' 
line 47231=>     'Better times, for Bree at any rate,' said Gandalf.  
line 47232=>     'I hope so, I'm sure,' said Butterbur. 'Well, this  has been the nicest  
line 47233=>chat I've  had  in  a month of  Mondays. And  I'll not deny that I'll  sleep 
line 47234=>easier  tonight and with a lighter heart. You've given  me a powerful lot to 
