line 47842=>rode off into the gathering night. The people cheered. 
line 47843=>     'All the same,' said Frodo to all those who stood near, 'I wish for  no 
line 47844=>killing; not even of the ruffians, unless  it must be done, to  prevent them 
line 47845=>from hurting hobbits.' 
line 47846=>     'All right! '  said Merry.  'But  we shall be having  a visit  from  the 
line 47847=>Hobbiton gang any time  now, I  think. They  won't come just to  talk things 
line 47848=>over.  We'll try to deal with them  neatly, but  we must be prepared for the 
line 47849=>worst. Now I've got a plan.' 
line 47850=>     'Very good,' said Frodo. 'You make the arrangements.' 
line 47851=>     Just  then  some hobbits, who had  been sent out towards Hobbiton, came 
