line 47954=>Will. So things went from bad to worse. There wasn't no smoke left, save for 
line 47955=>the Men;  and the  Chief didn't hold with beer, save for his Men, and closed 
line 47956=>all the inns;  and everything except Rules got  shorter and  shorter, unless 
line 47957=>one could hide a bit  of one's own  when the ruffians  went  round gathering 
line 47958=>stuff  up "for fair  distribution": which meant  they got it  and we didn't, 
line 47959=>except for the leavings which you could have at the Shirriff-houses,  if you  
line 47960=>could  stomach them.  All  very bad.  But since Sharkey came it's been plain  
line 47961=>ruination.' 
line 47962=>     'Who is this Sharkey?'  said Merry. 'I heard  one of the ruffians speak 
line 47963=>of him.' 
